        IMMEDIATELY_AFTER_KING_RANPERRE_HAD_QUELLED_THE_STRIFE               = 6873,  -- Immediately after King Ranperre had quelled the strife within the Kingdom, Erpalacion was sent by the king's orders on an expedition to the Outlands.
        IT_IS_WIDELY_SAID_THAT_THIS_EXPEDITION_SERVED                        = 6874,  -- It is widely said that this expedition served no strategic significance, and that King Ranperre merely feared the power of Erpalacion.
        HE_WAS_NEVER_HEARD_FROM_AGAIN_KING_RANPERRE                          = 6875,  -- He was never heard from again. King Ranperre apparently nodded in satisfaction when hearing the report from the returning soldiers...
        I_DO_NOT_BELIEVE_THIS_STORY_EVEN_IF                                  = 6876,  -- I do not believe this story. Even if there is some truth to the tale, there is unlikely to be a reappearance of the last dragoon. ...However, I have no evidence to support my views.
        I_WISH_TO_ASSIGN_YOU_THE_TASK_OF                                     = 6877,  -- I wish to assign you the task of gathering information on the attacks against the Royal Knights. The true culprit must be brought to justice. What say you?
        I_HAVE_A_TASK_FOR_YOU_I_WISH                                         = 6878,  -- I have a task for you. I wish you to gather information on the true culprit behind these attacks. Considering your profession, surely you wish to dispel these rumors that sully the honor of your fellow dragoon.
        WHAT_SAY_YOU_LEAVE_IT_TO_ME_OTHER                                    = 6879,  -- What say you? Leave it to me. Other duties call me.
        EMPTY_SUITS_OF_ARMOR                                                 = 6880,  -- Empty suits of armor...?
        SIR_RAHAL                                                            = 6881,  -- Sir Rahal!
        WHAT_ARE_YOU_COWERING_FOR_THESE_ARE_NOTHING                          = 6882,  -- What are you cowering for? These are nothing more than stumbling puppets!
        SIR_RAHAL_IT_MUST_BE_THE_GHOST_OF                                    = 6883,  -- Sir Rahal. It must be the ghost of the last dragoon, come to wreak his vengeance...
        MIND_YOUR_TONGUE_ARAMAVIONT_YOU_STAND_ON_CASTLE                      = 6884,  -- Mind your tongue, Aramaviont. You stand on castle grounds.
        YES_SIR_MY_APOLOGIES                                                 = 6885,  -- Yes, sir. My apologies.
        THESE_EMPTY_SHELLS_WILL_NOT_RISE_AGAIN_CLEAR                         = 6886,  -- These empty shells will not rise again. Clear these away, and not a word to anyone of this.
        YES_SIR                                                              = 6887,  -- Yes, sir!
        WE_MUST_GET_TO_THE_BOTTOM_OF_THIS                                    = 6888,  -- We must get to the bottom of this matter. Have you noticed anything strange these past few days?
        SOMEONE_TRIED_TO_STEAL_THE_BRAIS_OF_THE                              = 6889,  -- Someone tried to steal the brais of the last dragoon...? Well, that certainly qualifies. Start your investigation from there.
        YOU_MIGHT_TRY_ASKING_FOR_INFORMATION_FROM_THE                        = 6890,  -- You might try asking for information from the people at the Brugaire Consortium.
        I_CONCEDE_THAT_THIS_IS_A_PROBLEM_THAT                                = 6891,  -- I concede that this is a problem that only concerns the knights... However, I feel that someone outside our ranks, with some distance from events, has a better chance to grasp the whole picture. Tell me if you have a change of heart.
        THE_PEOPLE_AT_THE_BRUGAIRE_CONSORTIUM_MAY_HAVE                       = 6892,  -- The people at the Brugaire Consortium may have information concerning the brais of the last dragoon. I doubt they would agree with me, but the merchants there owe me a favor.
        THIS_HANDWRITING_THAT_S_WHAT_THIS_IS_ALL                             = 6893,  -- %! This handwriting... That's what this is all about! ...You must talk with Sir Balasiel on this matter.
        I_CANNOT_SPEAK_OF_IT_OR_RATHER_I                                     = 6894,  -- I cannot speak of it... Or rather, I do not wish to speak of it...
        YOU_MUST_TAKE_THIS_MATTER_TO_SIR_BALASIEL                            = 6895,  -- You must take this matter to Sir Balasiel. I cannot speak of it... Or rather, I do not wish to speak of it...
        ANCOLAIN_WAS_A_POWERFUL_WARRIOR_BUT_HE_LACKED                        = 6896,  -- Ancolain was a powerful warrior, but he lacked self-control. I bode my time until his return to the ranks... But never did I imagine things would come to this.
        SO_YOU_LEARNED_FROM_SIR_BALASIEL_THAT_YOUR                           = 6897,  -- So you learned from Sir Balasiel that your wyvern can sense Ancolain's location...based on the shadow of the thoughts that still cling to the letter. I only hope that he hasn't dabbled in any of the black arts that are practiced by those savages to the south.
        THE_MISUNDERSTANDING_THAT_LONG_SURROUNDED_KING_RANPERRE_AND          = 6898,  -- The misunderstanding that long surrounded King Ranperre and the last dragoon has now been cleared--and with it, the chaos that threatened the stability of the knights. You have my thanks.
        TALLYING_CONQUEST_RESULTS                                            = 6899,  -- Tallying conquest results...
