        THERE_WAS_A_CURSE_ON_THE_BEASTMEN_S                                  = 6978,  -- There was a curse on the beastmen's banner!
        THE_CURSE_OF_THE_BEASTMEN_S_BANNER_HAS                               = 6979,  -- The curse of the beastmen's banner has been lifted!
        THERE_IS_A_BEASTMEN_S_BANNER                                         = 6980,  -- There is a beastmen's banner.
        F_W_IO_W_IO                                                          = 7056,  -- *f#[W io%[W io[@#
        CG_JEG                                                               = 7057,  -- %&=|Cg%JEg@#
        AH_YOU_ARE_ARE_YOU_NOT_I_VE                                          = 7058,  -- Ah, you are %, are you not? I've heard word of you from the gatehouse. We've got a mission for you--a special mission.
        OUR_SCOUTS_SAY_THE_BEASTMEN_ARE_RISING_AGAIN                         = 7059,  -- Our scouts say the beastmen are rising again... Not just here, but in lands abroad. We want you to go to Bastok and Windurst and see how they fare.
        WHILE_THERE_YOU_CAN_BE_RECOGNIZED_BY_BOTH                            = 7060,  -- While there, you can be recognized by both nations, with %. Not a bad deal, is it?
        I_HEREBY_ORDER_YOU_ON_OFFICIAL_BUSINESS_VISIT                        = 7061,  -- I hereby order you on official business. Visit the two countries of Bastok and Windurst, and receive recognition as an adventurer.
        HERE_IS_A_LETTER_OF_INTRODUCTION_TO_THE                              = 7062,  -- Here is a letter of introduction to the consulates of San d'Oria. Just hand it to the consul, and they'll know what to do with you.
        THE_CONSULATE_WILL_GIVE_YOU_FURTHER_ORDERS_ONCE                      = 7063,  -- The consulate will give you further orders. Once both countries have given you official recognition, come back here. I will issue you your %.
        THIS_WILL_BE_YOUR_FIRST_JOURNEY_ABROAD_NO                            = 7064,  -- This will be your first journey abroad, %, no? None can tell what adventures await. Take care, and come home safe.
        FIRST_YOU_MUST_VISIT_THE_SAN_D_ORIAN                                 = 7065,  -- First you must visit the San d'Orian consulates in Bastok and Windurst. The consuls there will give you further orders.
        AH_IT_S_YOU_HOW_ARE_THINGS_IN                                        = 7066,  -- Ah, it's you, %. How are things in lands abroad? Come back once you've been officially recognized. I have every confidence in you.
        YOU_ARE_WITHIN_THE_WALLS_OF_CHATEAU_D                                = 7067,  -- You are within the walls of Chateau d'Oraguille, home of royalty. Conduct yourself accordingly.
        AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_BASTOK_ARE_YOU_WELL_YOU                           = 7068,  -- An adventurer from Bastok, are you? Well, you have my respect for coming all the way here.
        AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_WINDURST_ARE_YOU_WELL_YOU                         = 7069,  -- An adventurer from Windurst, are you? Well, you have my respect for coming all the way here.
        BUT_KNOW_YOU_THIS_OUR_KINGDOM_OF_SAN                                 = 7070,  -- But know you this: our Kingdom of San d'Oria has no intention of showing a friendly facade to either Bastok or Windurst.
        HOW_YOU_CLASSLESS_MOBS_COULD_EVER_THINK_TO                           = 7071,  -- How you classless mobs could ever think to stand shoulder-to-shoulder with the Elvaan is, frankly, beyond me.
        YET_ON_YOU_COME_IMPERTINENT_STUTTERING_SHRIMPS_LUMBERING             = 7072,  -- Yet on you come--impertinent stuttering shrimps, lumbering ore-heads, purring fur-balls! It's simply unacceptable.
        BUT_ENOUGH_OF_THAT                                                   = 7073,  -- But, enough of that...
        HERE_IS_YOUR_MISSION_INFILTRATE_GHELSBA_OUTPOST_NORTHWEST            = 7074,  -- Here is your mission: infiltrate Ghelsba Outpost, northwest of San d'Oria.
        IN_THE_MIDDLE_OF_THE_GHELSBA_CAMPS_IS                                = 7075,  -- In the middle of the Ghelsba camps is a place called the highland encampment. We want you to defeat the camp head, a Warchief Vatgit.
        YOU_LL_FIND_THE_ENCAMPMENT_A_LITTLE_WAYS                             = 7076,  -- You'll find the encampment a little ways into Ghelsba. Go in, cross the river, and you'll see the camps up on a ridge to the east.
        WHEN_YOU_VE_FINISHED_IF_YOU_AREN_T                                   = 7077,  -- When you've finished, if you aren't Orc fodder, report back to your own consulate. We don't take kindly to foreigners loitering around the chateau, if you get my meaning.
        THE_ORCS_AREN_T_SO_MUCH_OF_A                                         = 7078,  -- The Orcs aren't so much of a problem that the Kingdom need worry about sending out knights. Let the adventurers clean them up for pocket change--that is our policy.
        DON_T_MAKE_ME_REPEAT_MYSELF_GET_GOING                                = 7079,  -- Don't make me repeat myself. Get going.
        CONGRATULATIONS_BUT_DON_T_EXPECT_ANYTHING_FROM_US                    = 7080,  -- Congratulations, but don't expect anything from us. Our policy towards Windurstians and Bastokers can be summarized as detached cooperation, you see.
        AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_BASTOK_ARE_YOU_CONSUL_HELAKU                      = 7081,  -- An adventurer from Bastok, are you? Consul Helaku sent word about you. You look able, that's for sure.
        AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_WINDURST_ARE_YOU_CONSUL_KASARORO                  = 7082,  -- An adventurer from Windurst, are you? Consul Kasaroro sent word about you. You look able, that's for sure.
        WELL_YOU_MAY_NEVER_REACH_THE_GLORY_OF                                = 7083,  -- Well, you may never reach the glory of the Royal Knights, but do good work, and you'll be rewarded accordingly.
        HERE_IS_OUR_DILEMMA_THE_ORCS_HAVE_SET                                = 7084,  -- Here is our dilemma. The Orcs have set up a front-line base of operations in a place called Ghelsba Outpost, northwest of San d'Oria.
        YOU_RE_FAMILIAR_WITH_THE_QUADAV_NO_WELL                              = 7085,  -- You're familiar with the Quadav, no? Well, Orcs are just like them. A vicious and barbaric race, and quite stupid to boot.
        YOU_RE_FAMILIAR_WITH_THE_YAGUDO_NO_WELL                              = 7086,  -- You're familiar with the Yagudo, no? Well, Orcs are just like them. A vicious and barbaric race, and quite stupid to boot.
        THE_PROBLEM_IS_THOSE_ORCS_HAVE_BEEN_SHOWING                          = 7087,  -- The problem is, those Orcs have been showing signs of intelligence lately. They've started using ranged weapons...even machines of war!
        OUR_INVESTIGATIONS_INDICATE_THAT_SOMEONE_IS_BEHIND_THE               = 7088,  -- Our investigations indicate that someone is behind the Orcs, supplying them with weapons.
        WE_WANT_YOU_TO_FIND_A_CAVERN_DEEP                                    = 7089,  -- We want you to find a cavern deep in Ghelsba Outpost--a place called Yughott Grotto.
        WE_VE_SENT_MANY_AN_ADVENTURER_TO_YUGHOTT                             = 7090,  -- We've sent many an adventurer to Yughott Grotto, but few have returned, and we are desperate for knowledge.
        THERE_MAY_BE_SOME_DANGER_INVOLVED_BUT_IF                             = 7091,  -- There may be some...danger involved, but if you provide us with useful information, formal recognition from the Kingdom of San d'Oria will be yours.
        I_M_A_LITTLE_BUSY_HERE_REPORT_TO                                     = 7092,  -- I'm a little busy here. Report to your country's San d'Orian consulate when you've completed this mission.
        WELL_IT_S_GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_AGAIN                                      = 7093,  -- Well, %, it's good to see you again. Let's see the report you've brought back, then!
        THE_SHADOW_LORD_BACK_THAT_S_IMPOSSIBLE_HE                            = 7094,  -- The Shadow Lord...back!? That's impossible! He was slain by our forces in the Great War twenty years ago...
        WHAT_THE_NETHER_BEASTS_HAVE_BROKEN_OUT_INTO                          = 7095,  -- What!? The nether beasts have broken out into this land? This is dire news, indeed!
        IF_THIS_REPORT_IS_TRUE_WE_MUST_TAKE                                  = 7096,  -- If this report is true, we must take action.
        HMM_BUT_TO_BE_HONEST_I_FIND_IT                                       = 7097,  -- Hmm...but, to be honest, I find it hard to believe.
        VERY_WELL_I_WILL_TAKE_THIS_REPORT_YOU                                = 7098,  -- Very well. I will take this report. You will be issued %, as promised.
        YOUR_LATEST_ACCOMPLISHMENT_RAISES_YOUR_MISSION_RANK_TO               = 7099,  -- Your latest accomplishment raises your mission rank to 3. Congratulations.
        YOU_MUST_BE_WEARY_BE_AT_EASE_IN                                      = 7100,  -- You must be weary. Be at ease in this chateau. There is much here to soothe the mind and warm the spirit.
        I_VE_BEEN_WAITING_FOR_YOU_AS_YOU                                     = 7101,  -- I've been waiting for you, %. As you've probably already heard from the gatehouse, you are to report to the Embassy of San d'Oria at Jeuno.
        OUR_RELATIONS_WITH_JEUNO_ARE_VITAL_TO_MAINTAINING                    = 7102,  -- Our relations with Jeuno are vital to maintaining the balance of power between our Kingdom of San d'Oria, Windurst, and Bastok.
        YOU_WILL_RECEIVE_YOUR_LETTER_OF_INTRODUCTION_TO                      = 7103,  -- You will receive your letter of introduction to Jeuno from His Majesty Royaulais Destin himself. Great honor this is!
        PROCEED_THROUGH_THE_DOOR_TO_THE_AUDIENCE_CHAMBER                     = 7104,  -- Proceed through the door to the audience chamber. The king is waiting for you. Remember to mind protocol!
        YOU_HAVE_BEEN_GRANTED_AN_AUDIENCE_WITH_THE                           = 7105,  -- You have been granted an audience with the king.
        YOU_AUDIENCE_WITH_THE_KING_IS_FINISHED                               = 7106,  -- You audience with the king is finished.
        WHAT_IS_THE_MATTER_DO_NOT_KEEP_THE                                   = 7107,  -- What is the matter? Do not keep the king waiting!
        WELCOME_I_AM_DESTIN_KING_OF_SAN_D                                    = 7108,  -- Welcome, %. I am Destin, King of San d'Oria.
        PLEASE_BE_AT_EASE_I_VE_HEARD_OF                                      = 7109,  -- Please, be at ease. I've heard of you from Claidie. Much have you done for the Kingdom, it seems!
        AS_I_M_SURE_LORD_HALVER_HAS_TOLD                                     = 7110,  -- As I'm sure Lord Halver has told you, we decided to appoint you to serve in the Embassy of San d'Oria at Jeuno.
        RECENTLY_WE_LOST_ONE_OF_OUR_STAFF_THERE                              = 7111,  -- Recently we lost one of our staff there. But do not be alarmed, for you shall serve under my direct appointment.
        TAKE_THAT_LETTER_OF_INTRODUCTION_WITH_YOU_AND                        = 7112,  -- Take that letter of introduction with you and depart for Jeuno.
        THE_EMBASSY_HAS_BEEN_INFORMED_AND_IS_EXPECTING                       = 7113,  -- The embassy has been informed, and is expecting you. Show the letter to any of the staff there.
        DEPART_AS_SOON_AS_YOU_ARE_ABLE                                       = 7114,  -- Depart as soon as you are able.
        SAFE_JOURNEYS                                                        = 7115,  -- Safe journeys, %.
        GET_TO_JEUNO_AND_TAKE_THAT_LETTER_OF                                 = 7116,  -- Get to Jeuno, and take that letter of introduction with you. Ambassador Jima is anxious to see you!
        HELLO_YOU_VE_RUSHED_BACK_FROM_JEUNO_UPON                             = 7117,  -- Hello, %. You've rushed back from Jeuno upon hearing the news, right? Well, we've taken care of those bandits already.
        WELL_HALVER_IS_EXAGGERATING_AGAIN_WITH_TALK_OF                       = 7118,  -- Well, Halver is exaggerating again, with talk of a botched assassination. What could he mean by the king falling unconscious? Surely he is not calling adventurers to the chateau over such nonsense!
        SUCH_BRIGANDS_CANNOT_STAND_BEFORE_THE_MIGHT_OF                       = 7119,  -- Such brigands cannot stand before the might of the Temple Knights! His whisperings dishonor our nation. Do you not agree?
        CURILLA_ARE_YOU_THERE                                                = 7120,  -- Curilla? Are you there?
        YES_YOUR_MAJESTY                                                     = 7121,  -- Yes, Your Majesty!
        AH_VERY_GOOD_YOUR_LEADERSHIP_WAS_EXEMPLARY_AS                        = 7122,  -- Ah, very good. Your leadership was exemplary, as always. Thanks to you, I may focus on my duties.
        YOU_ARE_TOO_KIND_YOUR_MAJESTY                                        = 7123,  -- You are too kind, Your Majesty.
        HOWEVER_CURILLA_THERE_SEEMS_TO_BE_SOMETHING_YOU                      = 7124,  -- However, Curilla, there seems to be something you overlooked.
        YOUR_MAJESTY                                                         = 7125,  -- Your Majesty?
        DURING_THE_UPROAR_SOMEBODY_MADE_OFF_WITH_THE                         = 7126,  -- During the uproar, somebody made off with the talisman!
        THE_TALISMAN_YOUR_MAJESTY_NOT_THE_ONE_THAT                           = 7127,  -- The talisman, Your Majesty? Not the one that keeps the Shadow Lord imprisoned!
        THE_VERY_ONE_WE_WERE_VISITED_BY_AN                                   = 7128,  -- The very one. We were visited by an infiltrator while our eyes were on the brigands.
        SO_THE_INTRUDERS_WERE_BUT_A_DECOY                                    = 7129,  -- So, the intruders were but a decoy...
        I_SUSPECTED_THEM_SO                                                  = 7130,  -- I suspected them so.
        AND_WHO_MIGHT_KNOW_OF_THE_TALISMAN_S                                 = 7131,  -- And who might know of the talisman's existence, even among San d'Orians? Your Majesty, I fear someone bent on bringing the Shadow Lord back from his exile did this!
        BUT_BEFORE_WE_TRACK_DOWN_THIS_INFILTRATOR_FIRST                      = 7132,  -- But before we track down this infiltrator, first must we thwart their sinister plot. Halver, let us decide on a plan of action.
        CURILLA_BE_NOT_DISHEARTENED_BY_NO_MEANS_WAS                          = 7133,  -- Curilla, be not disheartened; by no means was this your fault. Call off the alert, and return to your regular duties.
        WELL_YOUR_HELP_IS_NEEDED_YET_AGAIN_HALVER                            = 7134,  -- Well, %, your help is needed yet again. Halver will convey my orders soon enough... Remember, you have our thanks!
        WE_SHALL_BEGIN_IMMEDIATE_DISCUSSION_ON_A_POLICY                      = 7135,  -- We shall begin immediate discussion on a policy for action. %, you must work on improving your skills and equipment.
        SPEAK_NAUGHT_OF_THE_ATTEMPT_ON_THE_KING                              = 7136,  -- Speak naught of the attempt on the king's life, nor of this business with the Shadow Lord, lest panic grip the Kingdom!
        WE_VE_COME_TO_A_DECISION_AT_LAST                                     = 7137,  -- We've come to a decision at last, %. We will send an expedition to the accursed Northlands.
        IT_WILL_GO_TO_THE_ANCIENT_RUINS_OF                                   = 7138,  -- It will go to the ancient ruins of Fei'Yin, northeast of the Beaucedine Glacier. Of course, you'll be going, too.
        THE_RUINS_ARE_THOSE_OF_A_CITY_BUILT                                  = 7139,  -- The ruins are those of a city built by an ancient civilization that we believe was more advanced than our own.
        THE_RACE_THAT_LIVED_THERE_CALLED_THEMSELVES_THE                      = 7140,  -- The race that lived there called themselves the Zilart. We have found similar ruins on Cape Teriggan to the south.
        AMAZINGLY_THEY_BOTH_REMAIN_THOUGH_THEY_WERE_BUILT                    = 7141,  -- Amazingly they both remain, though they were built long ago. It is as if some unseen force defies time to protect them.
        ONCE_THIRTY_YEARS_AGO_AN_INTERNATIONAL_EXPEDITION_WAS                = 7142,  -- Once, thirty years ago, an international expedition was sent to the Northlands. They were to uncover the secret of the Zilart's power.
        THEY_RETURNED_EMPTY_HANDED_WE_NEED_YOU_TO                            = 7143,  -- They returned empty-handed. We need you to head to the Beaucedine Glacier and scour the ruins of Fei'Yin yourself.
        THE_RUINS_ARE_OVERRUN_WITH_FIENDS_YOU_KNOW                           = 7144,  -- The ruins are overrun with fiends, you know. We captured it from the Shadow Lord twenty years ago at the cost of many lives.
        WE_SET_A_SEAL_ON_THE_RUINED_COLISEUM                                 = 7145,  -- We set a seal on the ruined coliseum to strengthen the barrier of the Northlands from the inside.
        YOU_MUST_FIND_IT_AND_USE_THIS_NEW                                    = 7146,  -- You must find it, and use this new seal to strengthen its magic if necessary.
        YES_I_M_CONCERNED_ABOUT_THE_SHADOW_LORD                              = 7147,  -- Yes, I'm concerned about the Shadow Lord's return. But if the border falls and the nether beasts pass into our realm, all in this world will fall to ruin.
        OF_COURSE_YOU_LL_BE_GOING_TOO                                        = 7148,  -- Of course, you'll be going, too.
        WELCOME_BACK_TIME_IS_OF_THE_ESSENCE_AS                               = 7149,  -- Welcome back, %. Time is of the essence, as you know, so I'll dispense with formalities. What did you find in Fei'Yin?
        SO_THE_SEAL_IN_FEI_YIN_WAS_ALREADY                                   = 7150,  -- So the seal in Fei'Yin was already broken... What will we do, should the nether beasts be brought to battle as they were twenty years ago?
        THE_ANSWER_IS_SIMPLE_HALVER_WE_MUST_BRING                            = 7151,  -- The answer is simple, Halver. We must bring the battle to them!
        BUT_YOUR_HIGHNESS_WE_LACK_KNOWLEDGE_OF_OUR                           = 7152,  -- But, Your Highness, we lack knowledge of our enemy. Though tempting, an attack would be far too dangerous.
        AN_ATTACK_WOULD_BE_MOST_EFFECTIVE_AT_THIS                            = 7153,  -- An attack would be most effective at this early stage! We need not worry about our forces, either. Plenty of reckless adventurers are willing to fight.
        BE_NOT_SO_HASTY_PRINCE_TRION                                         = 7154,  -- Be not so hasty, Prince Trion.
        CURILLA_WHAT_A_PLEASANT_SURPRISE                                     = 7155,  -- Curilla! What a pleasant surprise!
        PLEASE_CONSIDER_THE_ALLIANCE_WE_MUST_NOT_MOVE                        = 7156,  -- Please consider the alliance! We must not move troops beyond our borders without first consulting our allies.
        THE_ENEMY_IS_UPON_US_WE_VE_NO                                        = 7157,  -- The enemy is upon us! We've no time to chat with foreigners. We must act now!
        FORGIVE_ME_BUT_HOW_WILL_WE_EXPLAIN_THIS                              = 7158,  -- Forgive me, but how will we explain this, when it was our responsibility, as watchers of the Northlands, to stop our foes before they struck?
        IT_IS_NOT_OUR_DUTY_TO_EXPLAIN_TO                                     = 7159,  -- It is not our duty to explain to foreigners our kingdom's policies. We should move our forces now, so that no explanation will be needed!
        PLEASE_I_BEG_YOU_ASK_JEUNO_TO_GATHER                                 = 7160,  -- Please, I beg you! Ask Jeuno to gather the three great nations, and establish a unified front!
        SILENCE_CURILLA_SILENCE_SINCE_WHEN_HAVE_YOU_BECOME                   = 7161,  -- Silence, Curilla, silence! Since when have you become the weeping dove?
        PLEASE_LISTEN_TO_REASON_PRINCE_TRION_WE_HAVE                         = 7162,  -- Please, listen to reason, Prince Trion! We have but scarce information on the Shadow Lord's return, and what we do have has been collected by adventurers--it's unreliable at best!
        BUT_IF_THE_SHADOW_LORD_HAS_COME_AGAIN                                = 7163,  -- But if the Shadow Lord has come again, then we need the help of the other countries even more!
        I_HAVE_HEARD_ENOUGH_OF_YOUR_COOING_PRATTLE                           = 7164,  -- I have heard enough of your cooing prattle, Curilla! It is clear I can look to no one but myself for decisive leadership!
        WHERE_HAS_MY_DEAR_BROTHER_PIEUJE_HAS_GONE                            = 7165,  -- Where has my dear brother Pieuje has gone off to, and at such a critical time as this?
        COOING_PRATTLE                                                       = 7166,  -- Cooing...prattle?
        WITH_THE_RECONNAISSANCE_OF_FEI_YIN_COMPLETE_OUR                      = 7167,  -- With the reconnaissance of Fei'Yin complete, our kingdom must take action quickly. Unfortunately, with circumstances being what they are, I cannot issue orders for your next mission.
        I_BELIEVE_IT_WILL_TAKE_SOME_TIME_FOR                                 = 7168,  -- I believe it will take some time for us to reach a decision. Your time will come in due course, my friend. Until then, be well.
        POLITICAL_MANEUVERING_YOU_CALL_IT_TO_THINK_OUR                       = 7169,  -- Political maneuvering, you call it? To think our nation could become this cesspool of manipulation and intrigue...
        WE_HAVE_NO_TIME_FOR_THESE_ANTICS_IF                                  = 7170,  -- We have no time for these antics! If they truly are plotting to raise the Shadow Lord, we have not a moment to lose!
        THINGS_CANNOT_BE_ALLOWED_TO_PROCEED_AS_THEY                          = 7171,  -- Things cannot be allowed to proceed as they are. There must be a way to convince him...
        I_UNDERSTAND_HIS_LORDSHIP_S_FERVOR_BUT_THE                           = 7172,  -- I understand his lordship's fervor, but the risk is too great for us. I believe this requires utmost caution.
        AH_IS_IT_NOT_PRINCE_TRION_WAS_LOOKING                                = 7173,  -- Ah, %, is it not? Prince Trion was looking for you.
        HOW_LONG_DO_THESE_FOOLS_WISH_TO_SIT                                  = 7174,  -- How long do these fools wish to sit here discussing our deaths? We've no time for talk, not anymore.
        WE_MUST_MOVE_TO_STOP_THE_RETURN_OF                                   = 7175,  -- We must move to stop the return of the Shadow Lord, or war will come upon Vana'diel once again.
        THIS_IS_AN_ORDER_HURRY_AS_QUICKLY_AS                                 = 7176,  -- %, this is an order! Hurry as quickly as you can to Castle Zvahl in the far north, and put an end to this evil scheme of the beastmen!
        I_WILL_ACCEPT_ALL_RESPONSIBILITY_FOR_THIS_MISSION                    = 7177,  -- I will accept all responsibility for this mission. Now, go, brave warrior! For the future of Vana'diel!
        FOOLISHNESS_HE_WAS_DESTROYED_IN_THE_GREAT_WAR                        = 7178,  -- Foolishness! He was destroyed in the Great War, twenty years ago! They must have mistaken another fiend for him--that's what has happened, I'm sure of it!
        WHO_IS_THE_FOOL_HERE_IF_IT_TRULY                                     = 7179,  -- Who is the fool here? If it truly is him, then what? We would be facing far worse than the beastmen rabble then!
        THINK_BEFORE_YOU_SPEAK_BROTHER_IF_IT_IS                              = 7180,  -- Think before you speak, brother! If it is him, then why has he not shown himself these last twenty years?
        I_M_SAYING_WE_CANNOT_AFFORD_TO_TAKE                                  = 7181,  -- I'm saying we cannot afford to take that chance! This is more than an internal affair--we need to send an investigation party, immediately!
        WELCOME                                                              = 7182,  -- Welcome, %.
        I_AM_MISTARAVANT_I_HAVE_SERVED_AS_HEAD                               = 7183,  -- I am Mistaravant. I have served as head steward of this chateau for many a year.
        THIS_IS_THE_ROOM_OF_KING_DESTIN_NO                                   = 7184,  -- This is the room of King Destin. No place for the likes of you.
        DO_NOT_LOITER_INSIDE_THE_CHATEAU                                     = 7185,  -- Do not loiter inside the chateau.
        WHAT_S_THIS_I_LL_NOT_HAVE_MISCREANTS                                 = 7186,  -- What's this? I'll not have miscreants loitering in the chateau or its grounds! Go about your business, or be thrown out, the choice is yours.
        WHAT_S_THIS_WHAT_HAS_HAPPENED_HERE                                   = 7187,  -- What's this? What has happened, here?
        MA_R_LHAP_Q_F5D_LE_D_F1KE                                            = 7188,  -- MA%R*.LhAp#/%Q`$F5D"=LE%D"= F1kE h\7B
        Q_G_I_PE_7IH_AD_I_K                                                  = 7189,  -- q%(\&)%+)g i`pE` 7iH%AD(i>k$%%jqbA=g%\]o7)gHI
        G_IQ_YG_H_A_K_B                                                      = 7190,  -- ("%g;iq>%YG%H%A=>k$B
        RPI_VB_O9II                                                          = 7191,  -- ("%Rpi#VB\]o9II
        HERE_LIES_THE_BELOVED_QUEEN_LEAUTE_MAY_HER                           = 7192,  -- Here lies the beloved Queen Leaute. May Her Majesty's soul find Paradise.
        ME_NAME_S_CHALVATOT_I_BE_THE_GARDENER                                = 7193,  -- Me name's Chalvatot. I be the gardener here, you see.
        DON_T_RECKON_I_VE_SEEN_YOU_BEFORE                                    = 7194,  -- Don't reckon I've seen you before. A new recruit, are you?
        EH_I_M_BUSY_CAN_T_YOU_SEE                                            = 7195,  -- Eh? I'm busy, can't you see?
        WHAT_IS_THE_MATTER_CHALVATOT                                         = 7196,  -- What is the matter, Chalvatot?
        AH_YOUR_HIGHNESS_THIS_STRANGER_JUST_CAME_BARGIN                      = 7197,  -- Ah, Your Highness! This stranger just came bargin' in here, so I was about to tell--
        WAIT_I_VE_HEARD_OF_SOMEONE_LIKE_YOU                                  = 7198,  -- Wait... I've heard of someone like you.
        WHY_YOU_RE_A_NEW_ADVENTURER_ARE_YOU                                  = 7199,  -- Why, you're a new adventurer, are you not?
        MY_NAME_IS_CLAIDIE_I_D_ORAGUILLE                                     = 7200,  -- My name is Claidie I d'Oraguille.
        WHY_HE_SHE_S_BUT_A_VAGRANT_THERE                                     = 7201,  -- Why, he/she]'s but a vagrant! There's no need for Your Highness to address him/her] so!
        NOW_NOW_CHALVATOT_HE_SHE_HAS_COME_TO                                 = 7202,  -- Now, now, Chalvatot. He/She] has come to bolster the strength of our kingdom. Adventurers deserve our gratitude!
        YOU_ARE_ARE_YOU_NOT_FORGIVE_THIS_RUDE                                = 7203,  -- You are %, are you not? Forgive this rude reception.
        STRIVE_ALWAYS_FOR_THE_GLORY_OF_OUR_KINGDOM                           = 7204,  -- Strive always for the glory of our kingdom! May we meet again, %.
        HMPH_DON_T_YOU_GET_UPPITY_JUST_BECAUSE                               = 7205,  -- Hmph. Don't you get uppity, just because the princess saw fit to favor you with a few words. It don't mean a thing!
        I_M_BUSY_IF_YOU_DON_T_MIND                                           = 7206,  -- I'm busy. If you don't mind, I'd appreciate a little peace and quiet!
        THIS_GARDEN_BE_THE_MEMORIAL_GARDEN_FOR_OUR                           = 7207,  -- This garden be the memorial garden for our late Queen Leaute. She always loved flowers, and so she wanted to be buried here, you see.
        YOU_BE_AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_ABROAD_NO_IF                               = 7208,  -- You be an adventurer from abroad, no? If you've got a mission from the monarlais, you'd best be on it, quick.
        THAT_MONARLAIS_DON_T_LIKE_DEALING_WITH_YOU                           = 7209,  -- That monarlais don't like dealing with you foreigners much. Come to think of it, neither do I!
        I_AM_RAHAL_S_LEBRART_GENERAL_OF_THE                                  = 7210,  -- I am Rahal S. Lebrart, general of the Royal Knights of San d'Oria.
        THE_ROYAL_KNIGHTS_ARE_THE_SWORD_OF_SAN                               = 7211,  -- The Royal Knights are the sword of San d'Oria. Swiftly we strike, and wipe nests of fiends off the face of Vana'diel!
        WE_ARE_A_BAND_OF_WARRIORS_AND_SOME                                   = 7212,  -- We are a band of warriors, and some of us have been known to be...overzealous. But there's not a dark heart in the bunch of us. You have my word!
        I_VE_JUST_RETURNED_FROM_BASTOK_I_HAVE                                = 7213,  -- I've just returned from Bastok, I have. There be these Quadav living in the mine-holes there!
        BASTOKERS_DELVE_FOR_STONE_AND_LET_THE_QUADAV                         = 7214,  -- Bastokers delve for stone and let the Quadav be. But I says we should slay every last one of those shell-backed freaks!
        ROYAL_KNIGHT_ARAMAVIONT_REPORTING_I_VE_RETURNED_FROM                 = 7215,  -- Royal Knight Aramaviont reporting! I've returned from Windurst. Maybe it's just me, but the wee folk there are hiding something, I know it!
        WHY_ELSE_WOULD_THEY_LET_YAGUDO_RUN_WILD                              = 7216,  -- Why else would they let Yagudo run wild over the countryside? I'd lock those nasty feathered fowl up in cages if I were them!
        I_AM_CURILLA_V_MECRU_AND_THESE_ARE                                   = 7217,  -- I am Curilla V Mecru, and these are the Temple Knights' quarters. We are San d'Oria's shield, protecting the walls of the city from fiends.
        CHATEAU_AND_CITY_GUARDS_ALSO_BELONG_TO_THE                           = 7218,  -- Chateau and city guards also belong to the Temple Knights. Remember, we are here to serve and protect you.
        OF_COURSE_WE_HAVE_LITTLE_PATIENCE_WITH_UNSAVORY                      = 7219,  -- Of course, we have little patience with unsavory folk. Take care you're not mistaken for one.
        LEAVING_THE_CHATEAU                                                  = 7220,  -- Leaving the chateau?
        LEAVE_THE_CHATEAU_YES_NO                                             = 7221,  -- Leave the chateau? Yes. No.
        THEN_TAKE_CARE                                                       = 7222,  -- Then, take care.
        THEN_TAKE_YOUR_TIME                                                  = 7223,  -- Then, take your time.
        THE_DOOR_BEYOND_LEADS_TO_THE_TEMPLE_KNIGHTS                          = 7224,  -- The door beyond leads to the Temple Knights' quarters. The dungeons are down the corridor, to the left.
        THE_DOOR_BEYOND_LEADS_TO_THE_ROYAL_KNIGHTS                           = 7225,  -- The door beyond leads to the Royal Knights' quarters. Down the corridor to the right is the central garden.
        THE_AUDIENCE_CHAMBER_IS_BEYOND_NO_ENTRY_WITHOUT                      = 7226,  -- The audience chamber is beyond. No entry without permission!
        THE_AUDIENCE_CHAMBER_IS_BEYOND_ENTRANCE_BY_APPOINTMENT               = 7227,  -- The audience chamber is beyond. Entrance by appointment only.
        PLEASE_PROCEED_INTO_THE_AUDIENCE_CHAMBER                             = 7228,  -- Please proceed into the audience chamber.
        THE_DUNGEONS_LIE_BELOW_IF_YOU_RE_HERE                                = 7229,  -- The dungeons lie below. If you're here to see a prisoner, make it quick.
        NO_ENTRY_ALLOWED                                                     = 7230,  -- No entry allowed.
        BEYOND_THIS_HALLWAY_LIES_THE_QUEEN_LEAUTE_MEMORIAL                   = 7231,  -- Beyond this hallway lies the Queen Leaute Memorial Garden.
        PRINCESS_CLAIDIE_S_CHAMBERS_NO_ENTRY_ALLOWED                         = 7232,  -- Princess Claidie's chambers. No entry allowed.
        THIS_DOOR_LEADS_TO_THE_THRONE_IF_YOU                                 = 7233,  -- This door leads to the throne. If you've an appointment for audience, go around the front.
        THE_KING_S_CHAMBERS_ARE_BEYOND_IF_YOU                                = 7234,  -- The king's chambers are beyond. If you wish to see the king, schedule an appointment with Monarlais Halver.
        THIS_IS_THE_AUDIENCE_CHAMBER_ENTER_FROM_THE                          = 7235,  -- This is the audience chamber. Enter from the front if you have an appointment.
        PRINCE_TRION_S_CHAMBERS_NO_ENTRY                                     = 7236,  -- Prince Trion's chambers. No entry.
        PRINCE_PIEUJE_S_CHAMBERS_ARE_HERE_NO_ONE                             = 7237,  -- Prince Pieuje's chambers are here. No one allowed without permission.
        A_DECORATIVE_SUIT_OF_ARMOR                                           = 7238,  -- A decorative suit of armor.
        IT_S_LOCKED                                                          = 7239,  -- It's locked.
        IT_S_LOCKED_TIGHT                                                    = 7240,  -- It's locked tight.
        OBTAINED_KEY_ITEM_2                                                  = 7241,  -- Obtained key item: %!
