        FAR_HAVE_YOU_CARRIED_THIS_SO_I_SHALL                                 = 7475,  -- Far have you carried this, so I shall tell you the tale. But keep it secret, I beg you!
        AHEM_AGES_AGO_A_BARD_CAME_TO_SAN                                     = 7476,  -- Ahem! Ages ago, a bard came to San d'Oria. His voice was so stirring that songbirds would pause to listen.
        THE_KING_WAS_SO_MOVED_THAT_HE_SOUGHT                                 = 7477,  -- The king was so moved that he sought to keep him here in San d'Oria, if but for a day longer.
        THE_TALENTED_BARD_LINGERED_BUT_IN_DOING_SO                           = 7478,  -- The talented bard lingered. But in doing so, he stole the heart of the queen!
        YOU_SEE_HER_MARRIAGE_TO_THE_KING_WAS                                 = 7479,  -- You see, her marriage to the king was not for love, and she was many, many years his junior.
        BUT_STILL_ALWAYS_SHOULD_A_QUEEN_REMAIN_FAITHFUL                      = 7480,  -- But still, always should a queen remain faithful to her husband, don't you think?
        OFTEN_WOULD_THE_TWO_LOVERS_STEAL_AWAY_TO                             = 7481,  -- Often would the two lovers steal away, to find shelter from prying eyes.
        THEY_FORGED_A_PAIR_OF_RINGS_AND_PROMISED                             = 7482,  -- They forged a pair of rings, and promised to each other that they would become one in the next world.
        BUT_THEN_SUDDENLY                                                    = 7483,  -- But then, suddenly...
        THE_KING_GOT_WORD_OF_HER_INFIDELITY                                  = 7484,  -- The king got word of her infidelity!
        HIS_RAGE_AT_THE_LIAISON_BETWEEN_HIS_OWN                              = 7485,  -- His rage at the liaison between his own queen and his favorite minstrel knew no bounds. The bard was put to death by poison!
        BUT_NEVER_DID_THE_QUEEN_FORGET_HER_LOVER                             = 7486,  -- But never did the queen forget her lover.
        TO_PROPERLY_MOURN_HIM_SHE_SECRETLY_BADE_MY                           = 7487,  -- To properly mourn him, she secretly bade my elders craft burial ornaments.
        SHE_ADORNED_HIS_CORPSE_WITH_THEM_AND_CONVEYED                        = 7488,  -- She adorned his corpse with them, and conveyed the remains to Eldieme, and at last interred him there. Unfortunately, grave-robbers later came and ravaged his coffin, and scattered the ornaments in every direction!
        ERE_LONG_THE_KING_PASSED_AWAY                                        = 7489,  -- Ere long the king passed away.
        THE_QUEEN_THEN_LEFT_THE_PALACE_FOR_A                                 = 7490,  -- The queen then left the palace for a convent, where she quietly bode till the end of her days.
        HER_RING_WAS_GIVEN_TO_MY_FOREFATHER_AND                              = 7491,  -- Her ring was given to my forefather, and since then it was passed down to me.
        WITHOUT_A_DOUBT_THE_RING_YOU_HOLD_BELONGED                           = 7492,  -- Without a doubt, the ring you hold belonged to her lover, the bard!
        I_BELIEVE_THAT_THE_TWO_RINGS_SHOULD_BE                               = 7493,  -- I believe that the two rings should be together. Please, could you place them together upon the altar in the Monastic Cavern?
        HER_MAJESTY_S_INTERRED_THERE_AND_I_AM                                = 7494,  -- Her Majesty's interred there, and I am sure her spirit would be greatly pleased.
        TAKE_THE_RINGS_IT_S_THE_LEAST_I                                      = 7495,  -- Take the rings? It's the least I can do. I cannot.
        AT_LONG_LAST_HER_MAJESTY_S_WISH_SHALL                                = 7496,  -- At long last Her Majesty's wish shall come true! I suppose it's not proper and all, but my conviction says she would wish it.
