        YES_BUT_OUR_OBLIGATION_TO_THE_ALLIANCE_DENIES                        = 7660,  -- Yes, but our obligation to the alliance denies unilateral deployment to lands abroad. Were not the Northlands reduced to ashes in wars of old?
        THIS_DOES_NOT_BODE_WELL_VIGILANTLY_WE_WATCHED                        = 7661,  -- This does not bode well. Vigilantly we watched that land, and still this comes to pass!
        YES_I_AM_AFRAID_YOU_ARE_RIGHT_OUR                                    = 7662,  -- Yes, I am afraid you are right. Our eyes were on the comings and goings of Orcs, ignorant of the greater threat.
        AND_HOW_SHOULD_WE_EXPLAIN_THIS_TO_OUR                                = 7663,  -- And how should we explain this to our allies? San d'Oria cannot become the laughingstock of the civilized world!
        ARE_SUCH_WORDS_EVEN_NECESSARY                                        = 7664,  -- Are such words even necessary?
        PRINCE_TRION                                                         = 7665,  -- Prince Trion!
        BEFORE_THEY_HIT_US_LET_US_HIT_THEM                                   = 7666,  -- Before they hit us, let us hit them. A bold strike would hamper their momentum.
        BUT_MY_PRINCE_BY_SENDING_TROOPS_INTO_THE                             = 7667,  -- But, my prince! By sending troops into the Northlands, we expose ourselves to a certain degree of diplomatic liability...
        LIABILITY_FOOLS_ARE_YOU_ALL_BLIND_TO_THIS                            = 7668,  -- Liability!? Fools! Are you all blind to this peril? The enemy approaches while we bicker!
        YES_PRINCE_TRION_HOWEVER_WE_SHOULD_INVOLVE_THE                       = 7669,  -- Yes, Prince Trion... However, we should involve the king and Prince Pieuje in this decision.
        CURILLA_DO_YOU_SHARE_THE_OPINION_OF_HALVER                           = 7670,  -- Curilla, do you share the opinion of Halver and Rahal?
        YES_MY_PRINCE_WE_KNOW_NOT_THE_ENEMY                                  = 7671,  -- Yes, my prince. We know not the enemy's numbers. I believe the peril of rushing headlong into battle would be too great.
        INDEED_WORD_OF_THE_SHADOW_LORD_S_RETURN                              = 7672,  -- Indeed, word of the Shadow Lord's return was brought to us by adventurers, and is as yet unconfirmed.
        AND_IF_IT_DID_HAPPEN_TO_BE_TRUE                                      = 7673,  -- And if it did happen to be true, all the knights of San d'Oria would not be enough. We must confer with the alliance, my prince!
        HMPH_SO_BE_IT_ALL_THIS_TALK_OF                                       = 7674,  -- Hmph. So be it! All this talk of diplomatic liability... There are people we must defend, and an enemy we must defeat. Naught matters but that simple truth!
        IN_SUCH_TIMES_WHERE_COULD_PIEUJE_BE_GOING                            = 7675,  -- In such times, where could Pieuje be going?
        PRINCE_TRION_2                                                       = 7676,  -- Prince Trion...
        HMM_WE_MUST_MAKE_HASTE_AND_DECIDE_UPON                               = 7677,  -- Hmm... We must make haste and decide upon policy for our kingdom. At any rate, the exploration of Fei'Yin is complete.
        MUCH_TIME_MAY_BE_NEEDED_BEFORE_WE_REACH                              = 7678,  -- Much time may be needed before we reach a conclusion. Rest and prepare for other expeditions. And thank you for your dutiful service.
        AH_IT_IS_YOU_I_WAS_BEGINNING_TO                                      = 7679,  -- Ah, it is you, %. I was beginning to wonder who would be chosen for this next mission. You may proceed to the Audience Chamber.
        LONG_HAVE_WE_AWAITED_YOUR_ARRIVAL_YOUR_ASSISTANCE                    = 7680,  -- Long have we awaited your arrival, %. Your assistance is required in a mission for the Kingdom.
        WHERE_IS_THE_KING_YOU_ASK_HIS_HIGHNESS                               = 7681,  -- Where is the king, you ask? His Highness has retired to his quarters for the day. Recently, he has not been in the best of health.
        THERE_IS_NO_NEED_TO_BE_CONCERNED_WITH                                = 7682,  -- There is no need to be concerned with my father's condition. Now that Lightbringer has found its way back to San d'Oria, the king has begun to show great improvement. He should be back to his normal self within days.
        NOW_AS_FOR_THE_REASON_YOU_WERE_SUMMONED                              = 7683,  -- Now as for the reason you were summoned here: the papsque has called upon you to perform an investigation. His Holiness should be here shortly.
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_MY_TARDINESS                                         = 7684,  -- I apologize for my tardiness.
        I_HAVE_ASSEMBLED_YOU_ALL_HERE_TODAY_TO                               = 7685,  -- I have assembled you all here today to report a grave new finding.
        IT_SEEMS_AS_OF_LATE_A_MAGICAL_WALL                                   = 7686,  -- It seems as of late, a magical wall of sorts has been placed around San d'Oria.
        A_MAGICAL_WALL_YOU_SAY                                               = 7687,  -- A magical wall, you say?
        AND_WHAT_IS_MORE_THIS_BARRIER_GREATLY_RESEMBLES                      = 7688,  -- And what is more, this barrier greatly resembles the one that was utilized during the Great War to protect Tavnazia from its enemies.
        AN_ELEMENTAL_BARRIER_QUITE_ODD_TO_MY_KNOWLEDGE                       = 7689,  -- An Elemental Barrier... Quite odd... To my knowledge, only an heir to the Tavnazian throne would be able to procure such magic.
        ROCHEFOGNE_THAT_SCOUNDREL_IS_UP_TO_SOMETHING                         = 7690,  -- Rochefogne... That scoundrel is up to something.
        HOWEVER_WHAT_COULD_HIS_MOTIVES_BE_THIS_MAGIC                         = 7691,  -- However, what could his motives be? This magic wall--it has brought no harm to the Kingdom, has it?
        WHILE_THIS_IS_TRUE_THERE_ARE_STILL_MANY                              = 7692,  -- While this is true, there are still many aspects to this phenomenon that we do not understand. I feel it may be unwise to come to any hasty conclusions.
        AH_AND_THIS_IS_WHY_YOU_HAVE_REQUESTED                                = 7693,  -- Ah, and this is why you have requested the assistance of the adventurer %.
        THAT_IS_CORRECT_YOUR_HIGHNESS_TO_MAINTAIN_SUCH                       = 7694,  -- That is correct, Your Highness. To maintain such a wall, a medium is required at its center. While mediums differ depending on the type of magic used, I am positive that one is buried somewhere near San d'Oria.
        AND_ITS_LOCATION_IS                                                  = 7695,  -- And its location is?
        WITH_SAN_D_ORIA_AS_THE_CENTER_IT                                     = 7696,  -- With San d'Oria as the center, it can be assumed that three mediums have been buried. As far as I can ascertain, there would be one in each of the areas of Vollbow, Valdeaunia, and Norvallen...
        IF_IT_WERE_ME_I_WOULD_BURY_THEM                                      = 7697,  -- If it were me, I would bury them somewhere an adventurer would be least likely to travel...but where would that be?
        YOUR_HOLINESS_IT_SOUNDS_AS_IF_YOU_ARE                                = 7698,  -- Your Holiness, it sounds as if you are quite skilled at burying things...
        I_I_I_HAVE_CAST_MANY_A_MAGIC                                         = 7699,  -- I-I... I have cast many a magic wall in my time. I am just calling on my past experience.
        YOU_MUST_TAKE_EXTREME_CAUTION_IF_YOU_HAPPEN                          = 7700,  -- %, you must take extreme caution if you happen to come across the mediums. They must be disengaged in the correct order, and my instincts tell me that a trap may be set.
        ONCE_AGAIN_THE_PAPSQUE_HAS_IMPRESSED_US_ALL                          = 7701,  -- Once again, the papsque has impressed us all with his extensive knowledge on the situation at hand.
        YES_WELL_IS_ONE_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                        = 7702,  -- Yes. Well, % is one of San d'Oria's finest adventurers. I am certain that he/she] will locate the mediums and succeed in destroying them.
        MAY_THE_GODDESS_BLESS_YOU_WITH_HER_GRACE                             = 7703,  -- May the Goddess bless you with Her grace on your journey.
        WITH_THAT_ROCHEFOGNE_RUNNING_ABOUT_WE_WILL_BE                        = 7704,  -- With that Rochefogne running about, we will be forced to postpone the Rites of Succession. We would not want another scene like at the coming-of-age ceremony. We have our father's health to think about.
        HOWEVER_IF_WHAT_HE_SAYS_IS_TRUE_AND                                  = 7705,  -- However, if what he says is true, and he truly is the heir to the Marquisate, then that means we share the same blood...
        THAT_IS_CORRECT_MY_BROTHER                                           = 7706,  -- That is correct, my brother.
        CLAIDIE_YOU_KNOW_QUITE_WELL_THAT_YOU_ARE                             = 7707,  -- Claidie! You know quite well that you are not allowed to interfere with these meetings.
        HAVE_YOU_ALREADY_FORGOTTEN_I_HAVE_COMPLETED_MY                       = 7708,  -- Have you already forgotten? I have completed my coming-of-age ceremony. I have the right to attend.
        SHE_IS_CORRECT                                                       = 7709,  -- She is correct...
        HAH_I_APOLOGIZE_CLAIDIE_WELL_AS_LONG_AS                              = 7710,  -- Hah. I apologize, Claidie. Well, as long as you are present, let us hear your opinion on the situation at hand.
        AS_PIEUJE_HAS_JUST_STATED_ROCHEFOGNE_IS_OUR                          = 7711,  -- As Pieuje has just stated, Rochefogne is our uncle...our mother's younger brother.
        THAT_IS_IF_YOU_BELIEVE_THE_SCOUNDREL                                 = 7712,  -- That is, if you believe the scoundrel.
        AND_THAT_IS_THE_EXACT_REASON_WHY_IT                                  = 7713,  -- And that is the exact reason why it is necessary to sit down and discuss with him the matters before us.
        HIS_OUTBURST_AT_MY_COMING_OF_AGE_CEREMONY                            = 7714,  -- His outburst at my coming-of-age ceremony has enlightened me unto a piece of San d'Oria's terrible past.
        WATCH_WHAT_YOU_SAY_CLAIDIE_NOT_ALL_OF                                = 7715,  -- Watch what you say, Claidie. Not all of us here are of the royal family.
        I_HAVE_NOTHING_TO_HIDE_BROTHER_DURING_THE                            = 7716,  -- I have nothing to hide, Brother. During the Great War, the San d'Orian army led the beastman hordes to Tavnazia. San d'Oria used the Marquisate as a decoy.
        HOWEVER_THAT_DECISION_WAS_AN_IMPORTANT_TURNING_POINT                 = 7717,  -- However, that decision was an important turning point in the war. The gallant battle waged by the citizens of Tavnazia dealt a forceful blow to the beastman forces and gave us enough time to prepare our armies.
        YES_A_TURNING_POINT_THAT_MEANT_THE_LOSS                              = 7718,  -- Yes, a turning point that meant the loss of thousands of innocent lives and the end of a proud nation.
        TAVNAZIA_WAS_DESTROYED_WHEN_THE_BEASTMEN_S_SECRET                    = 7719,  -- Tavnazia was destroyed when the beastmen's secret weapon malfunctioned. Nothing, not even the beastmen themselves, were left after that calamity.
        THEN_WHY_DO_YOU_NOT_SIT_DOWN_WITH                                    = 7720,  -- Then why do you not sit down with Rochefogne and tell him this? Why must you capture him without being sure of his motives? Am I to believe this is how the royal family deals with its problems?
        CAN_YOU_NOT_REMEMBER_WHAT_TRANSPIRED_AT_YOUR                         = 7721,  -- Can you not remember what transpired at your coming-of-age ceremony? Rochefogne did not seem as if he wanted to sit down and chat over a cup of tea.
        THERE_MUST_HAVE_BEEN_SOME_REASON_SOME_REASON                         = 7722,  -- ... There must have been some reason... Some reason he could not tell us at that time...
        AND_THAT_IS_WHY_WE_MUST_FIRST_CAPTURE                                = 7723,  -- And that is why we must first capture him. Only then will we be able to clear up that which troubles our two sides.
        ALL_RIGHT_BUT_I_ASK_YOU_TO_PROMISE                                   = 7724,  -- All right, but I ask you to promise me one thing. Do not hurt Rochefogne when you capture him.
        HAH_I_WILL_HEED_YOUR_WISH_HOWEVER_IF                                 = 7725,  -- Hah. I will heed your wish. However, if he lays a hand on any of my knights, I will be forced to take action.
        YES_BROTHER_THAT_IS_ALL_I_HAVE_TO                                    = 7726,  -- Yes, Brother. That is all I have to say.
        SEARCH_OUT_AND_DESTROY_THESE_MEDIUMS_THAT_THE                        = 7727,  -- %, search out and destroy these mediums that the papsque mentioned earlier. Only by doing so will the Kingdom be safe from the treachery behind this fiendish plan.
        TRION_I_THINK_IT_IS_TIME_FOR_US                                      = 7728,  -- Trion. I think it is time for us to call on the services of the Cadavres des Corneilles.
        THE_CADAVRES_DES_CORNEILLES_PIEUJE_ARE_YOU_MAD                       = 7729,  -- The Cadavres des Corneilles! Pieuje, are you mad!?
        THINK_MY_BROTHER_IF_WE_ALLOW_ROCHEFOGNE_TO                           = 7730,  -- Think, my brother. If we allow Rochefogne to run about as he pleases, the consequences could be irreparable.
        IF_IS_ABLE_TO_DESTROY_THE_ELEMENTAL_BARRIER                          = 7731,  -- If % is able to destroy the Elemental Barrier, we can be sure that Rochefogne will be near. If we make the first move, we may be able to capture him.
        HMMM_THEN_DO_AS_YOU_WISH                                             = 7732,  -- Hmmm... Then do as you wish.
        I_ASK_THE_SAME_OF_YOU_THAT_I                                         = 7733,  -- I ask the same of you that I did my brothers. If you find Rochefogne, please do not harm him. He is trying to tell us something, I know it...
        SIGH_IF_THIS_IS_HOW_IT_IS_TO                                         = 7734,  -- <Sigh> If this is how it is to be, then I must take things into my own hands...
        HIS_MAJESTY_HAS_TAKEN_QUITE_ILL_OVER_THE                             = 7735,  -- His Majesty has taken quite ill over the past few days and is currently resting in his chambers. During his leave of absence from the throne, the two princes have taken his place. However, things should be running as smoothly as always.
        THE_PAPSQUE_IS_MOST_CERTAIN_THAT_THE_OBJECTS                         = 7736,  -- The papsque is most certain that the objects in question will be found in the areas of Vollbow, Valdeaunia, and Norvallen. You must treat this matter with the utmost delicacy. We cannot afford to have foreign powers taking advantage of our situation.
        AH_I_HAVE_ALREADY_READ_THROUGH_COTEAULEPOINT_S                       = 7737,  -- Ah, %. I have already read through Coteaulepoint's report. The fact that Rochefogne's body has not turned up troubles me; however, I must commend you on your efforts in disabling the Elemental Barrier.
        AS_FOR_THE_REMAINING_DETAILS_OF_WHAT_HAPPENED                        = 7738,  -- As for the remaining details of what happened...
        HOW_DO_YOU_REPLY_UNDERSTOOD_YOUR_HIGHNESS_REMAINING                  = 7739,  -- How do you reply? Understood, Your Highness. Remaining details?
        EXCELLENT_YOU_UNDERSTAND_WELL_THE_SENSITIVE_MATTERS_OF               = 7740,  -- Excellent. You understand well the sensitive matters of the Kingdom.
        DO_NOT_MOCK_ME_YOU_KNOW_QUITE_WELL                                   = 7741,  -- Do not mock me, %. You know quite well what I am speaking of.
        THE_EXISTENCE_OF_THE_CADAVRES_DES_CORNEILLES_MUST                    = 7742,  -- The existence of the Cadavres des Corneilles must remain a national secret. If news of this organization were to spread to the ears of the other nations, the consequences would be grave. And with our father as ill as he is...
        OUR_FATHER_IS_FEELING_MUCH_BETTER_NOW_HE                             = 7743,  -- Our father is feeling much better now. He should be returning to his proper position on the throne shortly.
        THE_RITES_OF_SUCCESSION_ARE_UPON_US_WHEN                             = 7744,  -- The Rites of Succession are upon us. When the time comes, we will be once again calling upon your services. You are dismissed.
        PIEUJE_WHAT_HAS_BECOME_OF_OUR_YOUNGER_SISTER                         = 7745,  -- Pieuje, what has become of our younger sister?
        SHE_HAS_SHUT_HERSELF_UP_IN_OUR_MOTHER                                = 7746,  -- She has shut herself up in our mother's garden...
        HMMM_SHE_MUST_REALIZE_THAT_WHAT_WE_ARE                               = 7747,  -- Hmmm... She must realize that what we are doing is for the good of the Kingdom.
        TRION                                                                = 7748,  -- Trion...
        WHAT_IS_IT_THAT_TROUBLES_YOU_PIEUJE                                  = 7749,  -- What is it that troubles you, Pieuje?
        WHAT_IF_WHAT_IF_NEITHER_OF_US_ARE                                    = 7750,  -- What if... What if neither of us are worthy enough to draw forth Lightbringer?
        HAH_HAH_HAH_YOUR_PETTY_WORRIES_AND_NIGGLING                          = 7751,  -- Hah hah hah! Your petty worries and niggling prudence amuse me, Brother.
        FEAR_NOT_AS_THERE_ARE_NONE_MORE_WORTHY                               = 7752,  -- Fear not, as there are none more worthy than we.
        ID_7753                                                              = 7753,  -- ...
        WHO_GOES_THERE                                                       = 7754,  -- Who goes there?
        AN_ORC_WHY_WOULD_AN_ORC_BE_HERE                                      = 7755,  -- An Orc? Why would an Orc be here? Hello? Is anyone around?
        THE_CADAVRES_DES_CORNEILLES                                          = 7756,  -- The Cadavres des Corneilles!?
        SO_THE_ORCS_HAVE_MADE_IT_THIS_FAR                                    = 7757,  -- So the Orcs have made it this far. Not surprising, with the magical wall being destroyed... This forces us to change our plans.
        WHY_YOU_DIRTY_SCOUNDREL_LEAVE_THIS_PLACE_AT                          = 7758,  -- Why, you dirty scoundrel! Leave this place at once! You have no right being here!
        I_APOLOGIZE_YOUR_HIGHNESS_HOWEVER_I_ASK_A                            = 7759,  -- I apologize, Your Highness. However, I ask a moment of your time to talk...
        YOU_WISH_TO_TALK_WITH_ME                                             = 7760,  -- You wish to talk...with me?
        WHO_WHO_ARE_YOU                                                      = 7761,  -- Who... Who are you?
        WITH_THE_RECOVERY_OF_THE_ROYAULAIS_THE_RITES                         = 7762,  -- With the recovery of the royaulais, the Rites of Succession will soon be upon us. The preparations for such an important ceremony will create many sleepless nights for those of us working here in the chateau.
        ROCHEFOGNE_WAS_SLAIN_IF_IT_WAS_NOT_ONE                               = 7763,  -- Rochefogne was slain? If it was not one of the Royal Knights, then... No, it is not possible...
        I_HAVE_HEARD_THE_RUMORS_OF_THE_FATE                                  = 7764,  -- I have heard the rumors of the fate of Rochefogne. However, I will not believe he is dead until I have seen the body with my own eyes.
        THE_RITES_OF_SUCCESSION_AT_LAST_OUR_NEW                              = 7765,  -- The Rites of Succession... At last our new leader will be chosen...
        WE_HAVE_INCREASED_THE_GUARD_FOR_THE_RITES                            = 7766,  -- We have increased the guard for the Rites of Succession twofold. We do not wish a repeat of the fiasco caused by Rochefogne at the coming-of-age ceremony.
        I_STILL_FEEL_RESPONSIBLE_FOR_LETTING_THE_SCOUNDREL                   = 7767,  -- I still feel responsible for letting the scoundrel near His Majesty. However, were it not for the events of that day, we would not be in our present position.
        I_STILL_LACK_THE_JUDGMENT_TO_KNOW_WHAT                               = 7768,  -- I still lack the judgment to know what is truth, and what is merely a lie...
        I_SEE_YOU_HAVE_ALL_ARRIVED_NOW_ALL                                   = 7769,  -- I see you have all arrived. Now all we have is to wait for Claidie.
        AH_HOW_IS_HE_HOW_IS_ROCHEFOGNE                                       = 7770,  -- Ah, how is he? How is Rochefogne?
        HE_IS_STILL_UNCONSCIOUS_WHILE_THE_BLOW_MISSED                        = 7771,  -- He is still unconscious. While the blow missed his vital organs, he has still sustained a great deal of damage. The doctors have told me that all we could do is watch and pray...
        I_SEE_THEN_WE_MUST_WAIT_UNTIL_WE                                     = 7772,  -- I see... Then we must wait until we may ask any more questions. However, I have just learned that the role of Lightbringer in the Rites of Succession was conceived by the papsque himself...
        HE_LIED_TO_US_ABOUT_THE_TRUE_INSCRIPTION                             = 7773,  -- He lied to us about the true inscription on the stone tablet. The true inscription speaks of how the sword must be protected at all times and must never be drawn.
        WHY_WOULD_THE_PAPSQUE_FABRICATE_SUCH_UNTRUTHS                        = 7774,  -- Why would the papsque fabricate such untruths?
        THE_PAPSQUE_HAD_COME_TO_BELIEVE_THAT_LIGHTBRINGER                    = 7775,  -- The papsque had come to believe that Lightbringer was the key to the Gates of Paradise. It seems as if the Archduke of Jeuno's brother, Eald'narche, led him to believe this...
        BECAUSE_THE_SWORD_CAN_ONLY_BE_DRAWN_BY                               = 7776,  -- Because the sword can only be drawn by a member of the royal family, His Holiness conceived the Rites of Succession.
        SO_THE_CEREMONY_WAS_A_FARCE                                          = 7777,  -- So the ceremony was a farce...?
        IT_CANNOT_BE_TRUE                                                    = 7778,  -- It cannot be true...
        WE_SHALL_NEVER_KNOW_THE_FULL_EXTENT_OF                               = 7779,  -- We shall never know the full extent of the papsque's ambition, but just like us, he was lured by the awesome power that Lightbringer harbors in its blade.
        THEN_WHAT_IS_LIGHTBRINGER                                            = 7780,  -- Then what...is Lightbringer?
        RIGHT_NOW_ALL_WE_CAN_BELIEVE_IS_WHAT                                 = 7781,  -- Right now, all we can believe is what Rochefogne has told us.
        LIGHTBRINGER_IS_THE_WEAPON_THAT_LAID_WASTE_TO                        = 7782,  -- Lightbringer is the weapon that laid waste to Tavnazia...
        WHATEVER_THE_CASE_WE_CANNOT_AFFORD_TO_LET                            = 7783,  -- Whatever the case, we cannot afford to let the beastmen attempt to use it, even if it takes the dispatch of every last soldier in San d'Oria.
        FATHER_LET_ME_TAKE_COMMAND_OF_THE_ARMY                               = 7784,  -- Father, let me take command of the army.
        TRION_2                                                              = 7785,  -- Trion...?
        I_AM_TO_BLAME_FOR_THE_LOSS_OF                                        = 7786,  -- I am to blame for the loss of Lightbringer. The responsibility of retrieving it lies within me.
        I_WAS_THE_ONE_WHO_IGNORED_CLAIDIE_S                                  = 7787,  -- I was the one who ignored Claidie's pleas to attempt negotiations with Rochefogne. If it were not for my foolish pride, none of this would ever have been brought upon San d'Oria! Father! Allow me the chance to redeem myself!
        CURB_YOUR_CONCEIT_TRION                                              = 7788,  -- Curb your conceit, Trion!
        FATHER_3                                                             = 7789,  -- Father...!?
        TRION_YOU_ARE_SIMPLY_DANCING_ON_THE_STAGE                            = 7790,  -- Trion, you are simply dancing on the stage of destiny. It is time for you to come down and face reality.
        FATHER_4                                                             = 7791,  -- Father...
        I_WILL_COMMAND_THE_ARMY                                              = 7792,  -- I will command the army.
        TRION_YOU_WILL_STAND_ON_THE_FRONT_LINES                              = 7793,  -- Trion, you will stand on the front lines and show the knights the true honor and valor of the d'Oraguille family.
        PIEUJE_YOU_WILL_MAINTAIN_THE_SUPPLY_ROUTES_PROVIDING                 = 7794,  -- Pieuje, you will maintain the supply routes, providing constant support to the front line and your brother.
        CLAIDIE_YOU_WILL_TEND_TO_ROCHEFOGNE_AS_WELL                          = 7795,  -- Claidie, you will tend to Rochefogne, as well as watch over him. He has yet to win my trust.
        AFTER_THIS_DISPLAY_YOU_MUST_THINK_THE_ROYAL                          = 7796,  -- %, after this display, you must think the royal family pitiful. However, I have one last request of you. I wish you to stand on the front lines with Trion.
        AND_FINALLY_WE_MUST_NOT_FORGET_THAT_WE                               = 7797,  -- And finally, we must not forget that we must be faithful to the citizens of this kingdom. We stand on the foundation they built. We must not lose their trust.
        YOUR_HIGHNESS_ONE_OF_OUR_SCOUTS_HAS_RETURNED                         = 7798,  -- Your Highness! One of our scouts has returned! The Orcs carrying Lightbringer have been spotted entering the Qu'Bia Arena!
        GOOD_WORK_TELL_THE_SCOUT_TO_REST_FROM                                = 7799,  -- Good work. Tell the scout to rest from his journey.
        I_ORDER_ALL_OUR_SOLDIERS_TO_FEI_YIN                                  = 7800,  -- I order all our soldiers to Fei'Yin! And tell them that the fate of San d'Oria rides on their bravery!
        WE_CAN_COUNT_ON_YOUR_ASSISTANCE_IN_OUR                               = 7801,  -- %! We can count on your assistance in our country's time of need, can we not? This is no longer a matter that can be handled by the royal family alone!
        IN_THE_YEARS_I_HAVE_SERVED_AS_A                                      = 7802,  -- In the years I have served as a Royal Knight, I have been sent on many missions. However, this expedition to Fei'Yin means much more to me than most have.
        I_DEDICATE_THIS_BATTLE_TO_THE_KNIGHTS_I                              = 7803,  -- I dedicate this battle to the knights I have lost. I will not let the blood they shed go in vain. We will defeat our enemies!
        IT_IS_TIME_FOR_THE_TEMPLE_KNIGHTS_AND                                = 7804,  -- It is time for the Temple Knights and the Royal Knights to put their differences aside for the good of the Kingdom. We must retrieve Lightbringer at all costs!
        LET_THIS_BATTLE_ONCE_AGAIN_BRING_GLORY_TO                            = 7805,  -- Let this battle once again bring glory to the Temple Knights!
        PRINCE_TRION_HAS_DEPARTED_FOR_FEI_YIN_MAY                            = 7806,  -- Prince Trion has departed for Fei'Yin. May the grace of the Goddess bring victory to the knights of the Kingdom!
        PRINCE_PIEUJE_HAS_LEFT_WITH_THE_EXPEDITION_TO                        = 7807,  -- Prince Pieuje has left with the expedition to Fei'Yin. I can only pray for his safety.
        PRINCE_TRION_HAS_RETURNED_SAFELY_AND_IS_CURRENTLY                    = 7808,  -- Prince Trion has returned safely and is currently awaiting your arrival in the Audience Chamber.
        PRINCE_PIEUJE_HAS_RETURNED_WITHOUT_INJURY_AND_IS                     = 7809,  -- Prince Pieuje has returned without injury and is awaiting your arrival in the Audience Chamber.
        I_NEVER_DOUBTED_YOUR_ABILITY_ON_THE_FRONT                            = 7810,  -- %! I never doubted your ability on the front line. We are truly in your debt. Proceed to the Audience Chamber. His Highness awaits!
        I_HAVE_HEARD_OF_YOUR_VALIANT_EFFORTS_FROM                            = 7811,  -- I have heard of your valiant efforts from my son. It would not be an understatement to say that your repeated bravery has helped maintain peace throughout the Kingdom.
        AS_FOR_LIGHTBRINGER_AS_LONG_AS_ROCHEFOGNE_REMAINS                    = 7812,  -- As for Lightbringer, as long as Rochefogne remains unconscious...
        YOUR_HIGHNESS_3                                                      = 7813,  -- Your Highness!
        AH_ROCHEFOGNE_CLAIDIE_HAS_KEPT_ME_INFORMED_ON                        = 7814,  -- Ah, Rochefogne. Claidie has kept me informed on your condition. How are you feeling?
        I_AM_IN_DEBT_TO_YOUR_FINE_DAUGHTER                                   = 7815,  -- I am in debt to your fine daughter for all she has done for me.
        YOUR_HIGHNESS_ALLOW_ME_TO_APOLOGIZE_FOR_ALL                          = 7816,  -- Your Highness... Allow me to apologize for all the trouble I have caused you and your kingdom.
        YOU_DO_SO_MUCH_RESEMBLE_YOUR_SISTER_FORGIVE                          = 7817,  -- You do so much resemble your sister... Forgive me. We all thought you had perished during the Great War. If I had only known that you were the true Rochefogne, we might have been able to prevent the loss of so many lives.
        YOUR_HIGHNESS_4                                                      = 7818,  -- Your Highness...
        YOU_MAY_RISE_ROCHEFOGNE_AS_MUCH_AS_I                                 = 7819,  -- You may rise, Rochefogne. As much as I would like to reminisce of times past, I first wish to know of Lightbringer.
        CERTAINLY                                                            = 7820,  -- Certainly.
        LONG_AGO_THE_DRAGON_KING_RANPERRE_ENTRUSTED_THE                      = 7821,  -- Long ago, the Dragon King, Ranperre, entrusted the Tavnazian Marquisate with the duty of protecting Lightbringer. All members of the royal family learn of this duty during their coming-of-age ceremony.
        SO_OUR_MOTHER_KNEW_AS_WELL                                           = 7822,  -- So our mother knew as well?
        YES_MY_SISTER_KNEW_OF_LIGHTBRINGER_SHE_ALSO                          = 7823,  -- Yes, my sister knew of Lightbringer. She also knew that the pollen of the dreamrose had the ability to temporarily neutralize the power of the blade.
        SO_THE_POLLEN_I_THREW_MY_MOTHER_LEFT                                 = 7824,  -- So the pollen I threw... My mother left it in her will for such circumstances!
        HOWEVER_WHILE_WE_KNEW_OF_OUR_DUTY_NONE                               = 7825,  -- However, while we knew of our duty, none in Tavnazia knew the true power of an unsheathed Lightbringer. We were simply told to never draw the mighty blade.
        BUT_WHEN_THE_BEASTMAN_FORCES_MADE_THEIR_WAY                          = 7826,  -- But when the beastman forces made their way to our castle gates...
        ON_THAT_FATEFUL_DAY_WHEN_THE_BEASTMEN_HAD                            = 7827,  -- On that fateful day when the beastmen had taken the city, my family made an attempt to escape to San d'Oria.
        HOWEVER_BEING_YOUNG_AND_PROUD_I_COULD_NOT                            = 7828,  -- However, being young and proud, I could not stand and watch as my country was engulfed in the flames of war. I seized Lightbringer from my father and headed back to the castle.
        I_NEVER_EVEN_MADE_IT_TO_THE_CITY                                     = 7829,  -- I never even made it to the city gates... The Orcs surrounded me, and that is when I drew Lightbringer from its sheath...
        AND_THE_MOMENT_I_DID_I_WAS_ENGULFED                                  = 7830,  -- And the moment I did, I was engulfed in a brilliant light. I felt as if I were almighty...as if I were a god...
        HOW_LONG_I_STOOD_THERE_I_DO_NOT                                      = 7831,  -- How long I stood there I do not remember. But when I came to, I was lying on a beach...and Lightbringer was nowhere to be found.
        THE_MAN_WHO_RESCUED_ME_FROM_THE_SEA                                  = 7832,  -- The man who rescued me from the sea told me how a great explosion had devastated Tavnazia, sending it deep underwater.
        HE_SAID_THAT_PEOPLE_ASSUMED_THE_CALAMITY_WAS                         = 7833,  -- He said that people assumed the calamity was caused by an Orc weapon that had self-destructed, but due to the lack of evidence, no one would ever know.
        THE_SHOCK_OF_THE_EXPLOSION_HAD_CAUSED_ME                             = 7834,  -- The shock of the explosion had caused me to lose my memory, and for years after that day, I believed the man's tale of the Orcs' secret weapon. But one day, like a flash of light, the memory of what I had done came back to me.
        BECAUSE_I_HAD_DRAWN_THAT_BLADE_NOT_ONLY                              = 7835,  -- Because I had drawn that blade, not only my family, but thousands upon thousands of innocent lives, were lost.
        FROM_THAT_DAY_FORTH_I_MADE_A_PLEDGE                                  = 7836,  -- From that day forth, I made a pledge to myself that I would not rest until I had found Lightbringer and returned her to her proper place. Only then would I be worthy to die and retreat to the hell that I deserve.
        TRULY_UNBELIEVABLE                                                   = 7837,  -- Truly unbelievable...
        I_SEE_SO_SAN_D_ORIA_S_PLAN                                           = 7838,  -- I see... So San d'Oria's plan to lure the beastman forces to Tavnazia worked because they were drawn to Lightbringer.
        BUT_WHY_WERE_YOU_ABLE_TO_SURVIVE_THE                                 = 7839,  -- But...why were you able to survive the explosion?
        WHILE_RUNNING_BACK_TO_THE_CITY_I_CAME                                = 7840,  -- While running back to the city, I came across a patch of beautiful dreamroses, and remembered my sister. I do not know why, but I picked one and put it in my breast pocket. I feel that is what might have saved me.
        HOWEVER_THE_LEGEND_OF_RANPERRE_TELLS_OF_HOW                          = 7841,  -- However, the legend of Ranperre tells of how the Dragon King used Lightbringer to bring peace to San d'Oria. How could such an instrument of good bring so much evil?
        THAT_I_DO_NOT_KNOW_THOUGH_I_FEEL                                     = 7842,  -- That, I do not know--though I feel that perhaps Lightbringer was not meant for us.
        WE_SHALL_RETURN_IT_TO_THE_LATE_KING                                  = 7843,  -- We shall return it to the late king and let him decide its fate.
        I_AGREE_AND_I_HAVE_THE_PERFECT_CITIZEN                               = 7844,  -- I agree. And I have the perfect citizen to help carry out the task.
        YOU_ARE_WELL_VERSED_IN_THE_LAYOUT_OF                                 = 7845,  -- %, you are well-versed in the layout of King Ranperre's Tomb. I ask you to travel there in advance and rid the area of any evil that could endanger the task at hand.
        I_HAVE_A_FEELING_THAT_THE_ORCS_MAY                                   = 7846,  -- I have a feeling that the Orcs may pay us another unexpected visit.
        PROCEED_TO_KING_RANPERRE_S_TOMB_WITH_CAUTION                         = 7847,  -- Proceed to King Ranperre's Tomb with caution. We must be on our guard until Lightbringer has been returned to its proper resting place.
        I_NEVER_THOUGHT_I_WOULD_LIVE_TO_SEE                                  = 7848,  -- %. I never thought I would live to see the day when the Royal Knights would fight alongside adventurers such as yourself. Your valiant efforts on the battlefield helped turn the tide in favor of San d'Oria.
        TO_PROTECT_THE_PRINCE_WHILE_GRAPPLING_WITH_THE                       = 7849,  -- To protect the prince while grappling with the enemy... I feel that even I may not have been able to accomplish such a feat. I applaud your skill.
        OUR_MISSION_IS_FINALLY_OVER_I_FEEL_THAT                              = 7850,  -- Our mission is finally over... I feel that sometimes we soldiers forget the frailty of life until we see it lost before our eyes on the battlefield.
        HOWEVER_THAT_GIVES_US_ALL_THE_MORE_REASON                            = 7851,  -- However, that gives us all the more reason to continue the fight. We cannot let those who have parted with us be forgotten. If you can spare a moment, journey to the cathedral and offer a prayer for the souls that gave their lives for the glory of the Kingdom.
        OH_WE_HAVE_BEEN_WAITING_FOR_YOUR_ARRIVAL                             = 7852,  -- Oh, %, we have been waiting for your arrival. His Highness is about give an address. Please take your position.
        I_KNOW_THAT_YOUR_BODIES_STILL_ACHE_FROM                              = 7853,  -- I know that your bodies still ache from our recent encounter with the Orcs.
        HOWEVER_I_REQUIRE_YOUR_UTMOST_ATTENTION_FOR_I                        = 7854,  -- However, I require your utmost attention, for I have an important announcement.
        I_HAVE_DECIDED_THAT_IT_IS_IN_THE                                     = 7855,  -- I have decided that it is in the best interest of the Kingdom to prolong the Rites of Succession indefinitely. My sons still have much to learn of ruling a kingdom. Furthermore, when the time comes for me to step down, if I find my sons inadequate, I will not hesitate in selecting an heir from outside the d'Oraguille family.
        IT_IS_NOT_ONLY_THE_ROYAL_FAMILY_BUT                                  = 7856,  -- It is not only the royal family, but others like %, that have silently supported San d'Oria for the past twenty years. Perhaps it is an adventurer such as he/she] that would be best suited for the throne.
        THE_ARROGANCE_OF_THE_ELVAAN_HAS_HELD_BACK                            = 7857,  -- The arrogance of the Elvaan has held back this country for much too long. From today forth, we shall recognize our fellow races and join hands with them to form a stronger, better kingdom.
        I_AM_AWARE_OF_THE_HARDSHIPS_YOU_HAVE                                 = 7858,  -- %. I am aware of the hardships you have had to face at the request of your country. However, you must realize that without your undying loyalty to the Kingdom, we would never have been able to realize our erring ways.
        WHILE_SIMPLE_ITEMS_CANNOT_EXPRESS_THE_GRATITUDE_THIS                 = 7859,  -- While simple items cannot express the gratitude this kingdom owes you, I hope you will accept this % with my blessing.
        WE_CAN_HOLD_OUR_HEADS_HIGH_KNOWING_THAT                              = 7860,  -- We can hold our heads high knowing that there are adventurers such as %, willing to risk their lives for the good of the Kingdom.
        NOW_IT_IS_THE_TIME_FOR_THE_CITIZENS                                  = 7861,  -- Now it is the time for the citizens of San d'Oria to do their part.
        THANKS_TO_YOUR_EFFORTS_THE_CHATEAU_REGAINED_THAT                     = 7862,  -- Thanks to your efforts, the chateau regained that sense of peacefulness that it had lacked for so long.
        I_MAY_HAVE_BEEN_STRICT_WITH_YOU_WHEN                                 = 7863,  -- I may have been strict with you when you were still a fledgling adventurer. However, I wish for you to forget all that. I now hold nothing but the uttermost respect for you.
        THERE_IS_STILL_MUCH_WORK_TO_BE_DONE                                  = 7864,  -- There is still much work to be done, but you may leave that to us. We do not wish to hold you back from new adventures that await you.
        NOW_THAT_LIGHTBRINGER_HAS_BEEN_SEALED_IN_THE                         = 7865,  -- Now that Lightbringer has been sealed in the Dragon King's tomb, the Orcs' activity has begun to dwindle. We will shortly be sending soldiers to rid the land of the remaining hordes.
        AS_MUCH_AS_YOUR_PRESENCE_ON_THE_FRONT                                = 7866,  -- As much as your presence on the front line would be welcomed, we cannot run to you to solve all our national crises.
        HOWEVER_I_EXPECT_THAT_ONE_DAY_THE_KINGDOM                            = 7867,  -- However, I expect that one day the Kingdom may again require your services. But until that day, may the light of the Goddess shine down upon you!
        THE_CONFLICT_WITH_THE_ORCS_MAY_BE_FINALLY                            = 7868,  -- The conflict with the Orcs may be finally coming to an end, but I doubt that instant peace will follow. We Temple Knights must remain alert at all times, lest danger rear its head within the boundaries of our noble kingdom.
        WOULD_YOU_NOT_CONSIDER_JOINING_OUR_RANKS_YOU                         = 7869,  -- %, would you not consider joining our ranks? You have much untapped potential.
        JOIN_THE_TEMPLE_KNIGHTS_YES_NO                                       = 7870,  -- Join the Temple Knights? Yes. No.
        WHILE_I_AM_FLATTERED_BY_YOUR_ENTHUSIASM_I                            = 7871,  -- While I am flattered by your enthusiasm, I know that you would not be satisfied if tied down by the duties of the knights. Your place is under the open skies of Vana'diel.
        AS_I_EXPECTED_I_KNOW_THAT_YOU_WOULD                                  = 7872,  -- As I expected. I know that you would not be satisfied if tied down by the duties of the knights. Your place is under the open skies of Vana'diel.
        NOW_GO_ADVENTURE_AWAITS                                              = 7873,  -- Now go! Adventure awaits!
        THE_BATTLE_TOOK_ITS_TOLL_ON_US_KNIGHTS                               = 7874,  -- The battle took its toll on us knights. I am relieved there won't be any more expeditions in the near future...but don't tell Sir Rahal I said that.
        LADY_CURILLA_AND_THE_TEMPLE_KNIGHTS_HAVE_FOUND                       = 7875,  -- Lady Curilla and the Temple Knights have found Lightbringer... Who would've thought that it would have been found in such a place?
        WE_KNIGHTS_MUST_KEEP_OUR_SENSES_SHARP_AND                            = 7876,  -- We knights must keep our senses sharp and our blades sharper. If we let either dull, it could mean our lives!
        THE_BATTLE_AT_FEI_YIN_DEALT_A_FIERCE                                 = 7877,  -- The battle at Fei'Yin dealt a fierce blow to the Orcs. I think that now is the time to finish those fiends off once and for all. The day of peace is finally here!
        THE_DEFEAT_OF_THE_SHADOW_LORD_SHOULD_IMPROVE                         = 7878,  -- The defeat of the Shadow Lord should improve the situation in the Northlands and improve our odds in the war with the Orcs.
        THERE_S_NOT_A_KNIGHT_IN_SAN_D                                        = 7879,  -- There's not a knight in San d'Oria that doesn't wish to take Lightbringer in his hands. However, there are still many mysteries that surround it...
        IT_S_NOW_TIME_TO_SHOW_THOSE_ORCS                                     = 7880,  -- It's now time to show those Orcs the true force of the Royal Knights. The battle will go down in history as the day we put an end to their fiendish plots!
        WHEN_I_WAS_IN_THE_NORTHLANDS_I_DIDN                                  = 7881,  -- When I was in the Northlands, I didn't know if I would ever be back here, sipping tea in the comforts of my quarters. I raise my glass to my colleagues who were not as fortunate...
        I_NEVER_KNEW_HIS_HIGHNESS_FELT_THAT_WAY                              = 7882,  -- I never knew His Highness felt that way about the Kingdom... To put the stability of the country ahead of bloodlines and tradition...the royaulais is truly a great leader.
        YOU_HAVE_MY_GRATITUDE_FOR_SAVING_MY_LIFE                             = 7883,  -- %, you have my gratitude for saving my life in the Qu'Bia Arena.
        THE_ROYAL_KNIGHTS_HAVE_DRIVEN_THE_ORCS_INTO                          = 7884,  -- The Royal Knights have driven the Orcs into a corner. Our conflict with fiends will soon be resolved. As much as I wish to stand on the frontline with my fellow soldiers, I have many new responsibilities to face here in the chateau.
        I_MAY_ONCE_AGAIN_REQUIRE_YOUR_SERVICES_UNTIL                         = 7885,  -- I may, once again, require your services. Until then, may the Goddess shine Her glory upon you in your travels.
        AS_MY_FATHER_STATED_YOU_MAY_BE_MORE                                  = 7886,  -- As my father stated, you may be more suited than I to rule our kingdom...
        HOWEVER_WHETHER_OR_NOT_I_EVER_STAND_AT                               = 7887,  -- However, whether or not I ever stand at the pinnacle of San d'Oria is not important. This situation with Rochefogne, Lightbringer, and the Orcs has taught me much of what I lack as a leader.
        FAR_TOO_OFTEN_I_HAVE_RELIED_ON_YOUR                                  = 7888,  -- Far too often I have relied on your bravery and loyalty. If it were not for your gallant actions, I would have surely perished in the Northlands.
        IF_YOUR_JOURNEYS_EVER_BRING_YOU_BACK_HERE                            = 7889,  -- If your journeys ever bring you back here to San d'Oria, you will always be welcome. Not as an adventurer, but as a friend.
        I_HAVE_HEARD_FROM_MY_BROTHER_OF_YOUR                                 = 7890,  -- I have heard from my brother of your bravery in Fei'Yin.
        YOUR_SUCCESS_ON_THE_BATTLEFIELD_NEVER_CEASES_TO                      = 7891,  -- Your success on the battlefield never ceases to amaze me. There is much I could learn from you...
        I_APPLAUD_YOU_ON_THE_COMPLETION_OF_THIS                              = 7892,  -- I applaud you on the completion of this mission, as well as apologize for constantly weighing your adventures down with new responsibilities.
        HOWEVER_YOUR_ACCOMPLISHMENTS_HAVE_BEEN_AND_WILL_BE                   = 7893,  -- However, your accomplishments have been, and will be, crucial for the prosperity of the Kingdom. I can sense that your love for San d'Oria is great.
        NOT_LENDING_OUR_EARS_TO_THE_THOUGHTS_AND                             = 7894,  -- Not lending our ears to the thoughts and opinions of others, only thinking that we are correct...
        HOWEVER_I_NOW_REALIZE_THAT_THIS_IS_THE                               = 7895,  -- However, I now realize that this is the sin we Elvaan are guilty of... That is why I ask of you to guide us. If you feel there is an error in our ways, do not hesitate to inform us.
        I_WILL_USE_YOUR_WORDS_TO_SHAPE_THIS                                  = 7896,  -- I will use your words to shape this country into a land that you, or your children, or your children's children will not be ashamed of.
        WHY_YOU_HAVE_BECOME_QUITE_THE_FIGHTER_SINCE                          = 7897,  -- Why, %. You have become quite the fighter since we last met. I can tell by merely glancing at your arms. Those are the limbs of someone who has spent many an hour polishing his/her] skills.
        HOWEVER_IF_YOU_WERE_TO_TAKE_PART_IN                                  = 7898,  -- However, if you were to take part in the Kingdom's tourneys, you would most certainly be defeated in the preliminary rounds.
        I_SENSE_A_HINT_OF_QUESTION_IN_YOUR                                   = 7899,  -- I sense a hint of question in your eyes. Let me explain... What separates the champions from the common folk lies in the acquisition of a single technique.
        THAT_TECHNIQUE_IS                                                    = 7900,  -- That technique is...
        LADY_CURILLA_WE_HAVE_COMPLETED_OUR_PATROL_OF                         = 7901,  -- Lady Curilla! We have completed our patrol of the perimeter! There is nothing to report!
        UNDERSTOOD_INFORM_THE_GUARDS_IN_WAITING_TO_BEGIN                     = 7902,  -- Understood. Inform the guards in waiting to begin their shift. You may rest in your quarters until you are summoned.
        YES_LADY_CURILLA                                                     = 7903,  -- Yes, Lady Curilla!
        UH_UM_LADY_CURILLA                                                   = 7904,  -- Uh...um...Lady Curilla?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_DO_YOU_HAVE_SOMETHING                               = 7905,  -- What do you want? Do you have something else to report?
        WH_WHO_MIGHT_THIS_ADVENTURER_BE                                      = 7906,  -- Wh-who might this adventurer be...?
        DO_YOU_MEAN_HIS_HER_SKILL_WITH_THE                                   = 7907,  -- Do you mean %? His/Her] skill with the single-handed blade has become quite renowned throughout the Kingdom. I am pondering over whether or not I should teach him/her] the final technique and recommend him/her] for the tourneys.
        THE_FINAL_TECHNIQUE_YOU_DON_T_THINK_HE                               = 7908,  -- The final technique!? You don't think he/she] could really...
        HAH_HAH_YOUR_TRAINING_FOR_THE_TECHNIQUE_TRANSFORMED                  = 7909,  -- Hah hah. Your training for the technique transformed you from a bumbling squire to the proud knight you are today. Who is to say that % will not be able to handle the trial?
        TH_THAT_IS_TRUE_BUT_BUT_IS_JUST                                      = 7910,  -- Th-that is true, but...but, % is just an adventurer. If he/she] were to be i-injured during the training, think of the repercussions...
        DO_I_LOOK_AS_IF_I_HAVE_NOT                                           = 7911,  -- Do I look as if I have not considered the repercussions? Do you wish to suggest that my judgment is erroneous? Now off with you! Sufficient rest is an essential part of your duties!
        Y_YES_MA_AM                                                          = 7912,  -- Y-yes, ma'am!
        SIGH                                                                 = 7913,  -- <Sigh>...
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THE_INTERRUPTION_HOWEVER_MY_OFFER                    = 7914,  -- I apologize for the interruption. However, my offer remains. If you wish to continue with your training in the way of the sword, I will assist. The knights may seem to think differently, but I assure you you need not worry.
        TAKE_THIS_SWORD_IT_WILL_BLESS_YOU_WITH                               = 7915,  -- Take this sword. It will bless you with its power until it senses that your skills have matured. Only then you will be ready to learn the final technique.
        WILL_YOU_PARTAKE_IN_THIS_TRIAL_I_WOULD                               = 7916,  -- Will you partake in this trial? I would be honored. Not just yet...
        POSITIVE_WAS_I_OF_YOUR_ANSWER_BEFORE_YOU                             = 7917,  -- Positive was I of your answer before you even spoke it. I can sense your desire for knowledge and power.
        NOW_TAKE_UP_IN_YOUR_HANDS_THIS_SWORD                                 = 7918,  -- Now take up in your hands this sword and begin your training.
        WHEN_YOU_FEEL_THAT_THE_SWORD_HAS_RECOGNIZED                          = 7919,  -- When you feel that the sword has recognized your might, return to me with the weakened blade. I will judge whether or not your journey is over.
        HOWEVER_THAT_IS_WHEN_THE_TRUE_TRIAL_WILL                             = 7920,  -- However, that is when the true trial will begin... I wish you luck, but you must remember it is not luck, but skill and perseverance, that will lead you back to this hall.
        SO_THERE_IS_STILL_DOUBT_IN_YOUR_HEART                                = 7921,  -- So there is still doubt in your heart. Irresolution can be a deadly thing on the battlefield. I advise you purge yourself of this trait before setting out on any more adventures.
        I_DO_NOT_YET_FEEL_THAT_THE_HAS                                       = 7922,  -- I do not yet feel that the % has recognized your true strength. You have much road yet to travel.
        AH_TRADE_ME_THE_SWORD_IF_YOU_WISH                                    = 7923,  -- Ah, %. Trade me the sword if you wish me to evaluate your progress. Or is there another reason why you have called?
        WHY_ARE_YOU_HERE_I_VE_MISPLACED_THE                                  = 7924,  -- Why are you here? I've misplaced the %. I wish to end my training. I apologize for the disturbance.
        THE_BLADE_THAT_YOU_HAVE_MISPLACED_WAS_SPECIALLY                      = 7925,  -- The blade that you have misplaced was specially ordered for the training of the San d'Orian knights. A large sum of the Kingdom's tax money was used to purchase it. What you have done could be considered a crime!
        SIGH_BUT_IT_WAS_I_WHO_MADE_THE                                       = 7926,  -- <Sigh> But it was I who made the decision to begin your training, therefore I will take responsibility for your actions this time. However, If you do not wish to travel to each and every one of our citizens' residences and make a personal apology for squandering their hard-earned gil, I suggest that you be more careful in the future.
        YOU_CANNOT_BE_SERIOUS_THINK_OF_THE_OPPORTUNITY                       = 7927,  -- You cannot be serious! Think of the opportunity you are passing by! I will give you one more chance...
        DO_YOU_REALLY_WANT_TO_END_YOUR_TRAINING                              = 7928,  -- Do you really want to end your training? I am positive. On second thought...
        EXCELLENT_I_AM_NOT_SURE_OF_YOUR_INTENTIONS                           = 7929,  -- Excellent. I am not sure of your intentions today, but if you were searching for kind words of moral support, you will not find them here. Such gibberish can only bind one and lead them to a false sense of success.
        I_SEE_I_HAVE_TRAINED_MANY_KNIGHTS_AND                                = 7930,  -- I see... I have trained many knights, and among them have been many who put down their swords just as you have. However, with time, those knights have faded into obscurity, their decision haunting them day in and day out.
        IF_YOU_DO_NOT_WISH_TO_JOIN_THEIR                                     = 7931,  -- If you do not wish to join their ranks, return here, and I will reconsider your training. I believe that you will make the correct decision.
        AH_YES_THIS_SWORD_SINGS_OF_YOUR_STRENGTH                             = 7932,  -- Ah yes, this sword sings of your strength and courageousness. I can see that you are ready for any challenge put forth before you.
        HOWEVER_AS_I_MENTIONED_BEFORE_THE_TRUE_TRIAL                         = 7933,  -- However, as I mentioned before, the true trial has yet to begin. It is now time to prove your skill. Normally we would send a pair of knights to complete this final task, but you are strong enough to take on the burden alone.
        TAKE_THIS_AND_SET_FORTH_TO_THE_QUICKSAND                             = 7934,  -- Take this % and set forth to the Quicksand Caves. There you shall find %. Be thorough in your preparations, as your greatest challenge awaits you.
        YOU_WILL_NO_LONGER_REQUIRE_THE_YOU_MAY                               = 7935,  -- You will no longer require the %. You may return it to me. I will watch over it as you continue your training. Good luck, and may the Goddess shine her light of grace upon you in battle.
        TAKE_THAT_AND_SET_FORTH_TO_THE_QUICKSAND                             = 7936,  -- Take that % and set forth to the Quicksand Caves. There you shall find %. Be thorough in your preparations, as your greatest challenge awaits you.
        I_APPLAUD_YOU_IN_YOUR_COMPLETION_OF_THE                              = 7937,  -- I applaud you in your completion of the trial. You now have acquired enough skill to wield the final technique.
        HOWEVER_YOU_MUST_NOT_BE_CONTENT_I_STILL                              = 7938,  -- However, you must not be content. I still feel that you are not yet ready for the grueling challenges that await you at the tourneys.
        I_REMEMBER_WHEN_I_TOOK_PART_IN_THE                                   = 7939,  -- I remember when I took part in the competition. I wanted to prove my power to the Kingdom. I wanted to prove that there was no one who could match me...
        HOWEVER_THAT_DISPLAY_WAS_ONLY_A_MEASURE_OF                           = 7940,  -- However, that display was only a measure of how weak I actually was...
        DURING_THE_CHAMPIONSHIP_MATCH_I_WAS_POSSESSED_WITH                   = 7941,  -- During the championship match, I was possessed with the lust for victory. That lust powered me, and when I brought down my blade onto Prince Trion, the force was so great that it shattered his weapon.
        BUT_AS_IT_SHATTERED_A_PIECE_OF_THE                                   = 7942,  -- But as it shattered, a piece of the broken sword flew into my left eye, darkening it for eternity. While I did not lose my life, I had lost something just as important to a knight--my eyesight.
        THOUGH_I_DID_NOT_LET_THIS_STAND_IN                                   = 7943,  -- Though I did not let this stand in my way. I continued my training, and just like you, acquired the final technique. And through my training, I learned to rely on more than that which reflects in the eye. I learned to feel what lies in my opponent's heart...
        I_SEE_THAT_THE_BATTLE_BETWEEN_YOU_AND                                = 7944,  -- I see that the battle between you and my brother is still being waged.
        P_PRINCE_PIEUJE_HOW_LONG_HAVE_YOU_BEEN                               = 7945,  -- P-Prince Pieuje! How long have you been...
        I_JUST_ARRIVED_CURILLA_I_WAS_BEGINNING_TO                            = 7946,  -- I just arrived, Curilla. I was beginning to wonder why our captain of the Temple Knights had failed to make her daily report.
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_MY_TARDINESS_IT_WILL_NEVER                           = 7947,  -- ...! I apologize for my tardiness! It will never happen again!
        IT_SEEMS_AS_IF_YOU_REMAIN_WEIGHTED_DOWN                              = 7948,  -- It seems as if you remain weighted down by the burdens you have placed upon your conscience.
        WEIGHTED_DOWN_AGAIN_I_APOLOGIZE_BUT_I_DO                             = 7949,  -- Weighted down... Again, I apologize, but I do not believe that is so.
        HAH_HAH_YOU_DIFFER_NOT_FROM_MY_DEAR                                  = 7950,  -- Hah hah. You differ not from my dear brother. The shards of the blade that shattered that day still remain lodged within your hearts.
        AND_SO_YOU_REMAIN_AT_A_DISTANCE_NEITHER                              = 7951,  -- And so you remain at a distance...neither of you the victor in your ongoing battle.
        ID_7952                                                              = 7952,  -- ...
        FORGET_WHAT_I_HAVE_SAID_I_WILL_BE                                    = 7953,  -- Forget what I have said. I will be waiting in my chambers for your report.
        YES_YOUR_HIGHNESS_2                                                  = 7954,  -- Yes, Your Highness.
        CURILLA_YOU_SAID_THAT_YOU_HAD_LEARNED_TO                             = 7955,  -- Curilla, you said that you had learned to feel what lies in your opponent's heart. I think that you had best spend some time pondering over those words once again. You may find that you have been missing their true meaning.
        I_KNOW_WHAT_THOSE_WORDS_MEAN_I_KNOW                                  = 7956,  -- I know what those words mean. I know exactly what they mean...
        I_DO_NOT_REGRET_LOSING_MY_EYE_IN                                     = 7957,  -- I do not regret losing my eye in that competition. I do not feel that I would be alive today, were it not for all I learned due to that accident.
        HOWEVER_EVERY_TIME_I_TAKE_UP_MY_SWORD                                = 7958,  -- However, every time I take up my sword, I can feel the dull, throbbing pain it brings to my soul.
        I_DO_NOT_WISH_FOR_YOU_TO_MAKE                                        = 7959,  -- I do not wish for you to make the same mistake as I... I apologize, but I have decided not to recommend you for the tourneys. I am sure there are other adventures more worthy of your newfound skill than a foolish game. I wish you all the best in your journeys, %.
        YOU_HAVE_LEARNED_THE_WEAPON_SKILL_SAVAGE_BLADE                       = 7960,  -- You have learned the weapon skill Savage Blade!
        AH_ADVENTURER_I_WAS_TOLD_OF_YOUR_COOPERATION                         = 7961,  -- Ah, adventurer. I was told of your cooperation in apprehending the thief.
        THE_INTERROGATION_IS_JUST_ABOUT_TO_BEGIN_IF                          = 7962,  -- The interrogation is just about to begin. If he is indeed guilty of the crime, you shall receive a reward.
        COME_WITH_ME                                                         = 7963,  -- Come with me.
        TWO_YEARS_AFTER_HIS_DEFEAT_AT_THE_SECOND                             = 7964,  -- Two years after his defeat at the Second Battle of Konschtat, King Raigegue massed his remaining knights in La Theine and awaited an opportunity to retaliate against Bastok.
        IT_WAS_AS_YOU_SAY                                                    = 7965,  -- It was as you say.
        HOWEVER_SEIZING_UPON_HIS_BROTHER_S_ABSENCE_PRINCE                    = 7966,  -- However, seizing upon his brother's absence, Prince Fellenant mobilized the Temple Knights and took control of the city of San d'Oria. He demanded a peace treaty be drawn up with Bastok, correct?
        THAT_IS_CORRECT                                                      = 7967,  -- That is correct.
        FEARING_AN_INTERNECINE_WAR_THE_KING_DECIDED_TO                       = 7968,  -- Fearing an internecine war, the king decided to send the Scepter Royaulais to Prince Fellenant and abdicate in his favor. His only condition was that the city be released from military control.
        YES_WE_WERE_ON_OUR_WAY_TO_BRING                                      = 7969,  -- Yes, we were on our way to bring the scepter to Prince Fellenant.
        WHEN_YOU_WERE_BESET_BY_A_WILD_STORM                                  = 7970,  -- ...When you were beset by a wild storm and took shelter within Ordelle's Caves...I believe this is how your story goes.
        AND_WHAT_MANNER_OF_ARTIFACT_IS_THIS_SCEPTER                          = 7971,  -- And what manner of artifact is this Scepter Royaulais you speak of?
        DO_YOU_NOT_KNOW_EVEN_THIS_IT_IS                                      = 7972,  -- Do you not know even this? It is a beautiful scepter with a rare jewel known as the Pierre Errante set at its end. It requires the most careful handling so as not to mar the stone.
        ID_7973                                                              = 7973,  -- ...
        WILL_YOU_ACCEPT_MY_WORDS_AS_TRUTH_NOW                                = 7974,  -- Will you accept my words as truth now? You must allow me audience with Prince Fellenant.
        DELUDED_FANTASIES_DO_YOU_HONESTLY_EXPECT_TO_FOOL                     = 7975,  -- Deluded fantasies... Do you honestly expect to fool us with this fabrication?
        HOW_DARE_YOU_YOU_ACCUSE_ME_OF_LYING                                  = 7976,  -- How dare you! You accuse me of lying!?
        THE_SECOND_BATTLE_OF_KONSCHTAT_KING_RAIGEGUE_AND                     = 7977,  -- The Second Battle of Konschtat? King Raigegue and Prince Fellenant? This goes beyond all patience!
        THEN_SIMPLY_WAIT_FOR_THE_ARRIVAL_OF_THE                              = 7978,  -- Then simply wait for the arrival of the Royal Knights who traveled with me--the Cardinal Stags! We were separated in Ordelle's Caves, but they should be arriving in the city at any moment.
        WELL_ISN_T_THAT_INTERESTING_CAPTAIN_GUICHANTMARGE_OF                 = 7979,  -- Well, isn't that interesting? Captain Guichantmarge of the Cardinal Stags is a good friend of mine, and I have no recollection of seeing your face among his troops when I performed an inspection. Neither do I recall hearing of any new recruits.
        SURELY_YOU_JEST_SIR                                                  = 7980,  -- Surely you jest, sir!
        THE_CAPTAIN_OF_THE_CARDINAL_STAGS_AS_ALL                             = 7981,  -- The Captain of the Cardinal Stags, as all should know, is Sir Plieucherot. Enough of these games!
        MONARLAIS_HALVER_WHAT_ARE_WE_TO_DO_WITH                              = 7982,  -- Monarlais Halver, what are we to do with this individual?
        HE_IS_OBVIOUSLY_NOT_THE_PERSON_SHOWN_IN                              = 7983,  -- He is obviously not the person shown in the sketch we have of the thief, nor do the guards of the royal treasury recognize him as the criminal. We cannot throw him into a cell merely because he has knowledge of the Scepter Royaulais.
        YET_WORD_OF_THAT_OTHER_MATTER_HAS_NOT                                = 7984,  -- Yet word of that other matter has not leaked beyond our walls. Are we to just let this man go...?
        HMMM_HOWEVER_I_DO_NOT_BELIEVE_THIS_FOOL                              = 7985,  -- Hmmm... However, I do not believe this fool would have had the finesse required to slip into the treasury. It was open for but a few moments when we removed that other object...
        MY_SINCEREST_APOLOGIES_SIR_WE_WERE_TAKEN_COMPLETELY                  = 7986,  -- My sincerest apologies, sir. We were taken completely unawares. Only one who had extensive knowledge of the castle could have evaded us in such a way... It was no ordinary burglar.
        DO_YOU_STILL_DOUBT_ME_I_AM_HERE                                      = 7987,  -- Do you still doubt me? I am here on orders from the king. Or is this how the prince treats envoys that appear on his doorstep?
        REMOVE_HIM_FROM_THE_CHATEAU_I_HAVE_NOT                               = 7988,  -- Remove him from the chateau. I have not the time nor the patience to deal with his delusions.
        SIR                                                                  = 7989,  -- Sir.
        I_AM_UNDER_ORDERS_FROM_THE_KING_WHAT                                 = 7990,  -- I am under orders from the king... What are you...? Release me at once!
        MARK_MY_WORDS_I_VIJARTAL_CAPHIEUX_HAVE_BEEN                          = 7991,  -- Mark my words! I, Vijartal Caphieux, have been insulted too many times this day! Your apologies will fall on deaf ears when next we meet!
        WAIT_ONE_MOMENT_WHAT_DID_YOU_JUST_SAY                                = 7992,  -- Wait one moment... What did you just say?
        I_SAID_TO_REMEMBER_THE_NAME_OF_VIJARTAL                              = 7993,  -- I said to remember the name of Vijartal Caphieux! I will never forget the disgraces I was forced to endure at your hands!
        THIS_IS_AN_OUTRAGE                                                   = 7994,  -- This is an outrage!
        THE_NAME_OF_THE_REVERED_HERO_OF_SAN                                  = 7995,  -- The name of the revered hero of San d'Oria used in vain by this common bandit! Have you no honor!?
        WHAT_IS_THIS_YOU_SPEAK_OF                                            = 7996,  -- What is this you speak of?
        SIMPLETON_THAT_IS_THE_NAME_OF_THE_GREAT                              = 7997,  -- Simpleton! That is the name of the great man who ended the war between the Royal and Temple Knights two hundred years ago! Even a child would not tell such a scandalous lie!
        GET_OUT_OF_MY_SIGHT_THE_NEXT_TIME                                    = 7998,  -- Get out of my sight! The next time you show your face in my presence, I will not be held responsible for my actions!
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_TWO_HUNDRED_YEARS_AGO                               = 7999,  -- What do you mean, two hundred years ago? Explain yourself. Why am I considered a hero...?
        I_AM_SORRY_BUT_I_CANNOT_PAY_YOU                                      = 8000,  -- I am sorry, but I cannot pay you a reward. He is not the man we are looking for.
        HOWEVER_WE_MUST_RETRIEVE_THE_SCEPTER_AT_ANY                          = 8001,  -- However, we must retrieve the scepter at any cost. It is an invaluable treasure. The symbol of San d'Oria.
        GIVE_THAT_GATE_GUARD_A_MESSAGE_FOR_ME                                = 8002,  -- Give that gate guard a message for me: he still has a chance to prove himself.
        AH_I_REQUIRE_YOUR_KEEN_EYE_AND_TIRELESS                              = 8003,  -- Ah, %! I require your keen eye and tireless endurance in a most important matter!
        YOU_SEE_I_WAS_SPEAKING_WITH_HIS_MAJESTY                              = 8004,  -- You see, I was speaking with His Majesty just the other day...
        YOU_SENT_FOR_ME_YOUR_MAJESTY                                         = 8005,  -- You sent for me, Your Majesty?
        HALVER_IT_IS_MOST_TROUBLESOME_THERE_IS_SOMETHING                     = 8006,  -- Halver, it is most troublesome. There is something I must confer with you about. Nay, rather I have a request for you.
        YES_YOUR_MAJESTY_2                                                   = 8007,  -- Yes, Your Majesty?
        AHEM_WELL_HOW_DO_I_BEGIN_DO_YOU                                      = 8008,  -- Ahem. Well, how do I begin? Do you recall the day when my beloved Leaute first came to the chateau?
        WHY_OF_COURSE_THE_CHATEAU_WAS_BUZZING_WITH                           = 8009,  -- Why, of course. The chateau was buzzing with rumors of the lovely Tavnazian princess that was destined to be our next queen.
        AT_THE_TIME_I_WAS_BUT_A_LOWLY                                        = 8010,  -- At the time I was but a lowly student, and I snuck out of a lecture to catch a glimpse of her noble countenance... In the end, I skipped the entire class to see the royal parade.
        I_MANAGED_TO_VIEW_QUEEN_LEAUTE_S_FAIR                                = 8011,  -- I managed to view Queen Leaute's fair profile from the gathered crowd. That image is still burned into my mind even now.
        I_NEVER_DREAMED_THAT_I_WOULD_END_UP                                  = 8012,  -- I never dreamed that I would end up working so closely with the beautiful princess I saw that day. Queen Leaute would always smile and have a kind word for me...
        HALVER_I_WASN_T_ASKING_YOU_FOR_A                                     = 8013,  -- Halver. I wasn't asking you for a rambling trip down memory lane.
        AH_MY_APOLOGIES_YOUR_MAJESTY_WAS_THIS_REQUEST                        = 8014,  -- Ah, my apologies, Your Majesty. Was this request related in some way to the queen?
        THIS_HAS_NOTHING_TO_DO_WITH_LEAUTE_I                                 = 8015,  -- This has nothing to do with Leaute. I wanted to speak with you about a new queen.
        AGAIN_I_MUST_APOLOGIZE_FOR_NOT_SEEING_STRAIGHT                       = 8016,  -- !!! Again, I must apologize for not seeing straight to the heart of the matter, Your Majesty.
        HRMPH_I_THOUGHT_PERHAPS_IT_WAS_TIME_THE                              = 8017,  -- Hrmph. I thought perhaps it was time the subject was broached.
        AH_WELL_YOUR_MAJESTY_HAS_BEEN_ALONE_FOR                              = 8018,  -- Ah... Well, Your Majesty has been alone for quite some time now. I am sure that your late wife would completely understand.
        YES_I_DO_NOT_DOUBT_THAT_LEAUTE_HAS                                   = 8019,  -- Yes, I do not doubt that Leaute has been uneasy in her eternal rest. Halver, I want you to search for a suitable lady to become the future Queen of San d'Oria.
        ME_YOUR_MAJESTY_I_I_AM_HONORED_THAT                                  = 8020,  -- Me, Your Majesty? I...I am honored that you would place that kind of trust in me, but I'm not sure... Ahem. If Your Majesty commands it, I will do my utmost to fulfill this duty.
        AND_WHAT_QUALITIES_WOULD_BE_DESIRABLE_FOR_THE                        = 8021,  -- And what qualities would be desirable for the lady to possess?
        HMMM_NATURALLY_SHE_MUST_HAVE_A_COMPASSIONATE_HEART                   = 8022,  -- Hmmm. Naturally, she must have a compassionate heart for all of our subjects, as did my dear Leaute.
        YOUR_MAJESTY_EVEN_NOW_YOUR_THOUGHTS_ARE_WITH                         = 8023,  -- Your Majesty, even now your thoughts are with her... It makes my heart ache to think of the loss you must be feeling.
        THIS_IS_A_SOMEWHAT_DIFFICULT_QUESTION_BUT_SHOULD                     = 8024,  -- This is a somewhat difficult question, but should the lady be blessed in appearance? A person of similar features to Queen Leaute?
        IT_IS_SAID_THAT_MEN_ALWAYS_LOOK_FOR                                  = 8025,  -- It is said that men always look for the image of their mother, however... These things you should be asking of the lady's future husband. Finding out his preferences will be part of this task.
        FIRST_I_MUST_TALK_TO_THE_FUTURE_HUSBAND                              = 8026,  -- First, I must talk to the future husband...
        FUTURE_HUSBAND_IMAGE_OF_THEIR_MOTHER_YOUR_MAJESTY                    = 8027,  -- ...Future husband? Image of their mother? Your Majesty, what exactly are we talking about here?
        HAVEN_T_YOU_BEEN_LISTENING_HALVER_WE_ARE                             = 8028,  -- Haven't you been listening, Halver? We are speaking of Trion's bride-to-be!
        OF_COURSE_IT_IS_YET_TO_BE_DECIDED                                    = 8029,  -- Of course, it is yet to be decided whether or not Trion is to succeed me. However, it is a distinct possibility. It will be necessary to find Pieuje a bride as well, but for the moment I believe we should search for a fitting consort for Crown Prince Trion.
        PRINCE_TRION_SO_THAT_IS_WHAT_THIS_IS                                 = 8030,  -- Prince Trion... So that is what this is all about. I thought our conversation peculiar...
        THE_ONLY_PECULIAR_THING_AROUND_HERE_IS_YOU                           = 8031,  -- The only peculiar thing around here is you, Halver! In any case, I entrust you with the duty of finding Trion a suitable wife and arranging an introduction.
        THIS_NEED_NOT_BE_SO_DIFFICULT_IF_TRION                               = 8032,  -- This need not be so difficult if Trion is merely made aware of the fact that he has approached a marriageable age.
        AHA_ONLY_I_HAVE_NEVER_SPOKEN_WITH_PRINCE                             = 8033,  -- Aha... Only, I have never spoken with Prince Trion on the subject of his...preferences.
        I_HAVE_IT_THIS_MAY_SEEM_PRESUMPTUOUS_OF                              = 8034,  -- ...I have it! This may seem presumptuous of me, but what of my own daughter? She is kindhearted and fair of face.
        SHE_HAS_PERHAPS_BEEN_OF_MARRIAGEABLE_AGE_FOR                         = 8035,  -- She has perhaps been of marriageable age for a little longer than usual, as I pondered which house would be the best for her to marry into...
        AHAHAHA_HALVER_HAVE_YOU_DEVELOPED_A_SENSE_OF                         = 8036,  -- Ahahaha! Halver, have you developed a sense of humor over the years?
        A_SENSE_OF_HUMOR_I_ASSURE_YOU_I                                      = 8037,  -- A sense of humor...? I assure you, I am most seriou--
        I_NEVER_THOUGHT_YOU_WERE_THE_TYPE_TO                                 = 8038,  -- I never thought you were the type to indulge in comedy. You must entertain us with your jests at the next banquet.
        NOW_AS_FOR_TRION_S_PREFERENCES_THIS_IS                               = 8039,  -- Now, as for Trion's preferences. This is quite a quandary, isn't it?
        ID_8040                                                              = 8040,  -- ...
        I_M_WELL_AWARE_OF_TRION_S_TASTE                                      = 8041,  -- I'm well aware of Trion's taste in ladies.
        PRINCE_PIEUJE                                                        = 8042,  -- Prince Pieuje...
        MY_BROTHER_S_PREDILECTIONS_ARE_OBVIOUS_IF_YOU                        = 8043,  -- My brother's predilections are obvious if you have spent as much time with him as I have.
        OF_COURSE_WHO_WOULD_KNOW_BETTER_THAN_HIS                             = 8044,  -- Of course, who would know better than his own brother? Well? Out with it then, Pieuje.
        MY_BROTHER                                                           = 8045,  -- My brother...
        HE_SEEMS_TO_THINK_THAT_A_WELL_TRAVELED                               = 8046,  -- He seems to think that a well-traveled, free-spirited adventurer would make the best partner for him.
        AN_ADVENTURER_I_MUST_SAY_THIS_IS_A                                   = 8047,  -- An adventurer! I must say, this is a surprise. I would have thought that a nobleman's daughter or the princess of a distant land would be more...
        HMM_THINGS_HAVE_CERTAINLY_CHANGED_SINCE_MY_DAY                       = 8048,  -- Hmm, things have certainly changed since my day. Mayhap this is the best choice for him. Halver, continue this discussion with Pieuje and seek out a girl that matches Trion's interests.
        PIEUJE_NOT_A_WORD_OF_THIS_TO_YOUR                                    = 8049,  -- Pieuje, not a word of this to your brother. He will become obstinate if he finds that we have been having this discussion without his knowledge.
        OF_COURSE_FATHER_I_AM_WELL_AWARE_OF                                  = 8050,  -- Of course, Father. I am well aware of his stubbornness.
        AND_THAT_IS_THE_PREDICAMENT_I_AM_IN                                  = 8051,  -- ...And that is the predicament I am in.
        AS_I_HAVE_EXPLAINED_WE_ARE_LOOKING_FOR                               = 8052,  -- %. As I have explained, we are looking for a fitting bride for Crown Prince Trion.
        ACCORDING_TO_PRINCE_PIEUJE                                           = 8053,  -- According to Prince Pieuje...
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_BLONDE_HAIR                     = 8054,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with blonde hair that almost hides the eyebrows and is tied back in a short ponytail.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_BROWN_HAIR                      = 8055,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with brown hair that almost hides the eyebrows and is tied back in a short ponytail.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_LONG_BLONDE                     = 8056,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with long blonde hair parted on the left and tied back in a ponytail.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_LONG_BLACK                      = 8057,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with long black hair parted on the left and tied back in a ponytail.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_FLOWING_SHOULDER                = 8058,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with flowing, shoulder-length black hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_FLOWING_SHOULDER_2              = 8059,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with flowing, shoulder-length chestnut-colored hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_BLACK                     = 8060,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short black hair brushed neatly over to the right.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_BLONDE                    = 8061,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short blonde hair brushed neatly over to the right.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_CROPPED                   = 8062,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short-cropped blonde hair that stands up in the front.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_CROPPED_2                 = 8063,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short-cropped brown hair that stands up in the front.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_LONG_BLACK_2                    = 8064,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with long black hair brushed over to the left.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_LONG_BROWN                      = 8065,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with long brown hair brushed over to the left.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_VERY_SHORT                      = 8066,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with very short, wavy brown hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_VERY_SHORT_2                    = 8067,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with very short, wavy blonde hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_BROWN                     = 8068,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short brown hair brushed to the right in the front, and tied in a small ponytail in the back.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_HUME_GIRLS_WITH_SHORT_BLONDE_2                  = 8069,  -- Prince Trion prefers Hume girls with short blonde hair brushed to the right in the front, and tied in a small ponytail in the back.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_SHOULDER_LENGTH               = 8070,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with shoulder-length blonde hair parted in the middle.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_SHOULDER_LENGTH_2             = 8071,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with shoulder-length red hair parted in the middle.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_PINNED_UP                     = 8072,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with pinned-up, braided silver hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_PINNED_UP_2                   = 8073,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with pinned-up, braided black hair.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_BLONDE_HAIR                   = 8074,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with blonde hair brushed to the right, and braided on the left.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_RED_HAIR                      = 8075,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with red hair brushed to the right, and braided on the left.
        PRINCE_TRION_PREFERS_ELVAAN_GIRLS_WITH_BLONDE_HAIR_2                 = 8076,  -- Prince Trion prefers Elvaan girls with blonde hair tied into two braids in the back.
